title: constantine_xi_(fate)
body:
[[Fate/Grand Order]]’s depiction of [[Constantine XI|Constantine XI Palaiologos]], introduced in the 2022 [[15-nin no Richiteki na Megane-tachi]] event under the alias "Michael". He was released as a Rider-class servant in the [[Traum (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. His name is localized as [b]Konstantinos XI[/b].

The final emperor of [[Byzantine empire|Byzantium]] before the [[Ottoman Empire]] captured Constantinople, he was famous for holding out against the prolonged siege and defending the city until his final breath. There is a legend surrounding Constantine called the Marble Emperor, where he purportedly turned to stone, unable to bear to look at the beloved seat of his empire falling to the enemy. He is also commonly considered to be the last Roman emperor, on the courtesy of Byzantium having evolved from the Eastern [[Roman Empire]].

He is the leader of the Reinstatement Realm in [[Traum (fate/grand order)|]]. During the singularity, he falls in love with [[Johanna (fate)|]].

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Kurahana Chinatsu]]
[b]Voice Actor:[/b] [[Kamio Shin'ichirou]]

title: charlemagne_(fate)
body:
One of the playable characters in [[Fate/EXTELLA LINK]]. Looks a lot like [[Fujimaru Ritsuka (male)|the male protagonist]] from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Charlemagne was incorporated into FGO as a playable Saber-class Servant during the [[Traum (fate/grand order)|]] chapter. His [[Charlemagne (Third Ascension) (fate)|third ascension]] is locked until players complete Traum.

[b]True Name:[/b] Charlemagne, King of Franks and Leader of the 12 Paladins. Specifically, this is the incarnation of the fantasy stories surrounding Charlemagne, whereas [[Karl Der Grosse (fate)|]] is the real Charlemagne as he was in life.

title: mio_(xenoblade)
body:
Deuteragonist of [[Xenoblade Chronicles 3]]. An Agnian off-seer in Colony Gamma. Best friends with [[Sena (xenoblade)|]].

She has a [[silver hair|silvery]]-[[white hair|white]] [[short hair|short]] [[bob cut]], [[yellow eyes]], and [[cat ears]]. Her main outfit includes a grey [[bomber jacket]] over a [[white tank top|white]] [[spaghetti strap]] [[tank top]], a white [[miniskirt]] with gold trim, [[black pantyhose|black]] [[pantyhose]]/[[leggings]], and white [[boots]]. Skirt and boots also feature additional [[red ribbon]] detailing.

She wields [[chakram]]s in battle, like [[Nia (xenoblade)|]] from [[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]].
She is also often seen with a [[flute]], which she uses for her mourning duties as off-seer.

[spoilers]It is strongly hinted that she is related to [[nia (xenoblade)|Nia]] and [[rex (xenoblade)|Rex]] from [[Xenoblade Chronicles 2]].[/spoilers]

title: united_states
body:
An image referencing the United States of America, most commonly showing the [[American flag]], depicting [[real world location]]s or [[politician]]s, or making jokes about American culture or American [[patriotism]].

The United States of America (commonly known as the United States, US, USA, or America), is a country primarily located in North America. It shares land borders with [[Canada]] to its north and with [[Mexico]] to its south and has maritime borders with the [[Bahamas]], [[Cuba]], [[Russia]], and other nations. Its national language is [[english_text|English]], though there is no legally official language except in some individual US states.

Do not apply this tag if the character is simply wearing [[American flag print]] clothing, unless the post explicitly references American culture in general.

title: bulletproof_(invincible)
body:
Zandale Randolph, also known by his hero alias Bulletproof, is a supporting character in Robert Kirkman's [[Invincible (series)|]] comic series and Amazon's animated adaptation.

He is known for briefly filling in as Invincible, on account of his similar powers, when [[Mark Grayson]] was busy on Planet Viltrum.

As it was a brief internet meme, a black (African-descended) character wearing Invincible's iconic yellow suit most likely is or references Bulletproof, therefore qualifying for this tag

title: ramune
body:
A carbonated soft [[drink]] sold in Japan, typically in "Codd-neck bottles":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Codd-neck_bottle], which use a glass marble as a stopper to keep the drink carbonated. The original formula is lemon-lime; nowadays there are many other flavors as well. At least one manufacturer labels it "Ramuné" for the North American market, indicating how it's meant to be pronounced. 

For the game and anime, use the tag [[Lamune]].

title: katsushika_hokusai_(third_ascension)_(fate)
body: [[Katsushika Hokusai (fate)|]] in her Third Ascension form from [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Her eyes change from blue to red, and her skin becomes a pale grey color. Her hair is covered in bulbous, eldritch-like decorations, one of which is actually [[Toto-sama (fate)|]] hiding upside-down on one of the red bulbs (this can be seen when you use her Quick card from a distance). She wears a black dress resembling octopus tentacles, and black sleeves that are connected directly to the dress. She doesn't have any legwear or footwear covering her legs. She swaps her weapon from a giant paintbrush to a series of smaller paintbrushes with different colors. Her personality also changes, likely because it is the original Hokusai himself taking over Oui's body.

title: katsushika_hokusai_(swimsuit_saber)_(fate)
body:
Swimsuit version of [[Katsushika Hokusai (fate)|]], though technically it is Katsushika Oui wearing the swimsuit. [[Toto-sama (fate)|]] consistently remains the same, wearing swimming goggles and having long tentacles on the sides of his head. Her Noble Phantasm is "Shokoku Taki-meguri", a consecutive attack set against the backdrop of multiple paintings of waterfalls.

Carries three katana, and one western sword, which Oui and her father wield with great proficiency. Personality-wise, this is Oui during her youth, where she enjoyed reading yomihon and dreaming of being a sword-wielding heroine.

Obtainable as a welfare servant during the [[Kenzan! Las Vegas Gozenjiai]] event.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Kuroboshi Kouhaku]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Yukana]] (Katsushika Oui)

title: servant_summer_festival!_2018
body:
[b]Eternal Tropical Summer Altar: Luluhawa[br]Servant Summer Festival! 2018[/b]
[quote]Chaldea has detected a Foreigner in the Hawaiian Islands.
To make matters even stranger, Servants have begun to disappear from Chaldea!
Concerned by the seriousness of the situation, Master is dispatched with several Servants as a protection detail.
There, a bizarre battle in the tropics erupts.

A summer festival of the Servants, by the Servants, for the Servants—the Servant Summer Festival—is about to begin![/quote]

A limited time [[Summer]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on August 9, 2018 and on the NA server on August 3, 2020. [[Jeanne d'Arc Alter (Swimsuit Berserker) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: alice_in_wonderland_(tim_burton)
body: [b][i]Alice In Wonderland[/i][/b] is a 2010 American Gothic dark fantasy adventure film directed by Tim Burton from a screenplay written by Linda Woolverton and produced by [[Disney|Walt Disney Pictures]]. The film stars Mia Wasikowska, Johnny Depp, Anne Hathaway, Matt Lucas, Helena Bonham Carter, and Crispin Glover, and features the voices of Alan Rickman, Stephen Fry, Michael Sheen, and Timothy Spall. A live-action adaptation and re-imagining of Lewis Carroll's works, the film follows [[Alice Kingsleigh]], a nineteen-year-old who accidentally falls down a rabbit hole, returns to Wonderland, and alongside the [[Tarrant Hightopp|Mad Hatter]] helps restore the White Queen to her throne by fighting against the Red Queen and her Jabberwocky, a dragon that threatens Wonderland's residents.

She is portrayed with [[very long hair|floor-length]] [[blonde hair]] with an [[ahoge]] and tied into [[twin braids]], [[green eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. 

Her default outfit consists of a [[frills|frilled]] [[white shirt]] top with a frilled [[blue capelet]] and a [[red ribbon]], blue [[corset]], [[white skirt]], frilled [[white thighhighs]], [[blue gloves]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[rudder footwear]]. title: blunt_tresses
body:
Hair that has been separated from the rest into [[sidelocks]], [[ringlets]], etc., and then been freshly cut flat. Typically tied with a [[tress ribbon]] or bunched together to create a tassel-like appearance. [[Akashi (kancolle)|Akashi]] from [[kantai collection|Kancolle]] is a prominent example of someone with these.

Not to be confused with [[blunt ends]], which refers to straight-cut hair in the back.

h4. Examples

* !post #8130294

h4. See also

* [[blunt ends]]

title: nattou
body:
A Japanese food made of fermented soybeans, commonly eaten for breakfast. Stirring them produces lots of spiderweb-like strings.

A lot of people are disgusted by its strong smell and sticky texture, especially when it's cheaply made or no longer fresh.

title: homer_simpson
body:
[b]Homer Jay Simpson[/b] is one of the main characters of the American animated sitcom [[The Simpsons]].

Homer and his wife [[Marge Simpson|Marge]] have three children: [[Bart Simpson|Bart]], [[Lisa Simpson|Lisa]] and [[Maggie Simpson|Maggie]]. As the family's provider, he works at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant as safety inspector.

He is a [[bald]] [[fat]] man with a [[beard]] who wears a [[white shirt]] and [[blue pants]].

title: ijichi_nijika
body:
Character in [[Bocchi the Rock!]].

She has [[brown eyes|brown]]/[[red eyes|red]] eyes and [[very long hair|very long]] [[blonde hair]] stylized in a [[side ponytail]], [[sidelocks]] & [[ahoge]] (often depicted as a [[detached ahoge]]). She usually wears the [[shimokitazawa high school uniform]] consisting of a [[long sleeves|long sleeved]] [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]], [[red bowtie]], and a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt]] with [[white socks]] & [[red shoes|red]] [[sneakers]]. She [[playing instrument|plays]] on the [[drum set]] and wears a [[short sleeves|short sleeved]] [[black shirt]] with [[suspenders|suspender]] [[brown pants]] while performing.

Has an older sister, [[Ijichi Seika]].

title: akikawa_yayoi_(umamusume)
body:
Supporting character from [[Umamusume]]. Chairwoman of Tracen Academy, voiced by [[Mizuhashi Kaori]].

A [[petite]] girl with [[brown hair]] and a [[white streaks|white streak]] running off center through her bangs and a conspicuous longer white hairlock from the left side of her head. Often depicted carrying a [[folding fan]] and wearing a [[sun hat]] with a horseshoe-shaped cutout on the brim and a blue ornamental rose in front, to the right side of her head. Usually has a black-and-white cat riding on top of her hat.

The Chairwoman has a distinctive speaking style; she tends to insert a lot of two-kanji idiomatic phrases (as full sentences) in her speech. This is usually reflected in English translations by using short, curt 1-2 word sentences.

While she was always important in the background of the game scenarios, it's only with the "Great Food Festival" scenario that she became able to personally contribute to the player's training as the host of that scenario.

Due to her color scheme and hat (and the cat riding on top of said hat, plus said cat's color scheme), fans have speculated that she is actually [[Northern Taste (racehorse)|]] under a human guise. As such, she is sometimes drawn as a [[horse girl]] with her hat off. Either way, the fact that the rose is near where [b]the right ear[/b] of a horse girl should be is important.

h4. Appearance

* !post #5859827

h4. Related characters

* [[Hayakawa Tazuna]] - Her secretary [spoiler]and likely another horse girl in a human guise[/spoiler].
* [[Matikanetannhauser (umamusume)|]] - [spoiler]Real life child[/spoiler]

title: palkia
body:
A Water/Dragon-type Legendary [[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]], #0484 in the National Pokédex.

A white and purple theropod-like creature. Has [[red eyes]], [[black sclera]]e, and a round plate on each shoulder that each have a [[pearl (gemstone)|]] in the center and a [[wings|wing]] on the back. The mascot of [[pokemon dppt|Pokémon Pearl]] and [[pokemon bdsp|Shining Pearl]]; its counterpart is [[Dialga]].

It has the power to control space itself. Alongside Dialga and [[Giratina]], it is a member of the "creation trio." All three were created by [[Arceus]]. The [[Lustrous Globe]] (not to be confused with the [[Lustrous Orb]]) allows it to change into its [[palkia (origin)|Origin Forme]].

title: secret_medicine_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Secret Medicine[/b], known as [b]Secret Potion[/b] in English prior to Generation VIII, is an item in the [[pokemon|Pokémon]] series. Unlike standard [[Potion (pokemon)|]]s, it is not a spray bottle, but rather a [[pouch]] of round [[pill]]s.

The item plays a role in three storylines across the series:

* In the Johto games ([[pokemon gsc|Gold, Silver, Crystal]], [[pokemon hgss|HeartGold, and SoulSilver]]), it is used to cure [[Jasmine (pokemon)|]]'s [[Ampharos]].
* In the Sinnoh games ([[pokemon dppt|Diamond, Pearl, Platinum]], [[pokemon bdsp|Brilliant Diamond, and Shining Pearl]]),  is used to heal a flock of [[Psyduck]].
* In [[pokemon legends: arceus|Legends: Arceus]], it is used to heal a different flock of Psyduck.

h4. External links
* "Bulbapedia":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Secret_Medicine]

title: langley_ii_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the [i]Independence[/i]-class USS [i]Langley[/i] (CVL-27) in [[Azur Lane]]. Not to be confused with [[Langley (Azur Lane)|her namesake predecessor, CV-1]], although it is specified that Langley II has the body and memories of the original Langley but with [i]Independence[/i]-class equipment and abilities. 

As she is basically the original [i]Langley[/i] with a new rig, her physical attributes remain unchanged ([[long hair|long]] [[green hair]], [[brown eyes]], [[small breasts]], wearing [[glasses]]) except a slight height increase. 

Her outfit as an [i]Independence[/i]-class light carrier is now composed of a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[shirt tucked in]], [[black jacket]], striped [[necktie]], [[black skirt|black]] [[pencil skirt]], [[black thighhighs]] with [[garter straps]], [[black footwear|black]] [[rudder footwear]], and [[black gloves]]. Her new [[rigging]] comprises two halves of her [[flight deck]], one on each side, with two [[anti-aircraft gun]]s per rig and operating a mix of newer wartime aircraft with older biplanes from her previous form.

title: icha_icha_(naruto)
body:
Icha Icha (イチャイチャ, English TV: Make Out) is a series of adult novels written by [[Jiraiya (Naruto)|]] after the commercial failure of The Tale of the Utterly Gutsy Shinobi. The Icha Icha novels are based on Jiraiya's experiences in love, particularly his rejections by [[Tsunade (Naruto)|]]. When he's working on a new novel, he gathers "research" by peeping on women while they bathe. Teenagers are often curious about the books' contents, prompting their parents and other adults to go to great lengths to keep the books away from them.
Icha Icha is wildly popular, giving Jiraiya's checkbook a balance that is "filled with zeroes". [[Hatake Kakashi]] is a particular fan of the series; he enjoys reading the books even while in the middle of conversations.

h4. External links
* "Narutopedia: Icha Icha":https://naruto.fandom.com/wiki/Icha_Icha

title: birmingham_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the US Navy light cruiser USS [i]Birmingham[/i] (CL-62). Character design by [[Pavapo]], voiced by Watabe Sayumi.

In-game, she has [[short hair with long locks]], colored [[red hair|red]], with matching [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[white cloak]] like her sister [[Montpelier (Azur Lane)|]], and beneath that is a [[blue dress]] with [[black gloves]] and [[thighhighs]]. She also sports a [[blue hairband]] with an [[anchor hair ornament]].

Her rigging is the standard [i]Cleveland[/i]-class setup with the 15.2 cm triple mounts on one side and 12.7 cm twin mounts on the other.

Sometimes paired with Princeton for historical reasons: the battle of Leyte Gulf where she, alongside [[Reno (Azur Lane)|]], stood by the stricken carrier [[Princeton (Azur Lane)|]] and took on her survivors.

title: montpelier_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the light cruiser USS [i]Montpelier[/i] (CL-57) in [[Azur Lane]]. Character design by [[Huanxiang Heitu]], voiced by [[Takahashi Rie]].

She has [[very long hair|very long]] silvery-[[grey hair]] with [[hair flaps|flaps]], and [[red eyes]]. She also wears a [[white cape]] like her sisters [[Cleveland (Azur Lane)|]] and [[Birmingham (Azur Lane)|]], a [[black shirt]] partially hidden by the cape and a red [[armband]] on the left sleeve, and black [[thighhighs]] with her name printed on it.

Her [[rigging]] is the standard [i]Cleveland[/i]-class battle rig, with two 15.2 cm triple mounts on one side and two 12.7 twin mounts on the other, with two [[Oerlikon 20mm gun]]s on the side below the 15.2 cm mounts.

She is often depicted with three particular sister ships: [[Cleveland (Azur Lane)|]], [[Columbia (Azur Lane)|]], and [[Denver (Azur Lane)|]]. They are called in-game the "Solomon Knights" and were known as Cruiser Division 12 (CruDiv12) in real life. Montpelier is the first in the class, as she was historically the CruDiv's flagship.

title: columbia_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the US Navy light cruiser USS [i]Columbia[/i] (CL-56) in [[Azur Lane]]. Character design by [[Hao (patinnko)|]], voiced by Horigome Saya.

In-game, she is portrayed having [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[red eyes]], with [[sunglasses]] on her head. She is wearing a blue-white shirt with a [[star print]], [[dog tags]], [[blue shorts]], [[brown belt]], and a striped [[single thighhigh]] on her left leg. Her [[rigging]] is the same as her sisters, with two 15.2 cm triple mounts on one side and two 12.7 cm twin mounts on another. Unlike [[Montpelier (Azur Lane)|]], she does not have 20 mm Oerlikon AA guns on her rig.

She is also shown [[chewing gum|chewing on bubble gum]] in her base art. In real life, Columbia was among the first of her class to enter service alongside Cleveland, Montpelier, and Denver (the so-called "Solomon Knights"/Cruiser Division 12).

title: cleveland_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the light cruiser USS [i]Cleveland[/i] (CL-55) in [[Azur Lane]]. Character design by [[Hao (patinnko)|]].

She has [[blonde hair]] in either a [[ponytail]] or [[one side up]], [[small breasts]], and [[red eyes]]. Her outfit consists of a fire-control director holding up her sidetail, a [[white cape]], [[blue jacket]], a very small [[miniskirt]], and star-spangled [[socks]].
Her [[rigging]] is the standard for her class, with two 15.2 cm triple mounts on the left and two 12.7 cm twin mounts on the right.

Cleveland is often nicknamed "Clevedad" by Chinese players, a carryover from [[world_of_warships|World of Warships]], similar to [[Belfast (azur lane)|]]'s nickname "Payfast" used by Western players, and also bears the nickname "Clevebro" due to her tomboyish and cavalier attitude.

title: trapdoor_springfield
body:
The "Trapdoor Springfields", named due to their distinctive hinged breechblock that opened like a trap door, are the collective name for a series of weapons created by the Springfield Arsenal from 1865 to 1903. The Model 1873 pattern was the first breech-loading [[rifle]] adopted as standard-issue for the United States Military. Due to budget concerns and the overwhelming amount of muzzle-loading [[musket]]s filling government storage after the [[American Civil War]], the Arsenal elected to base their weapons on the existing patterns, rather than creating a wholly new design. 

Visually, the Trapdoor Springfields of all types still resemble their Civil War-era heritage with an obvious [[caplock]] hammer on the side, but the large Allin hinged breech-block is the distinguishing feature. Trapdoor Springfields saw use during the Indian Wars, [[Spanish-American War]], and Philippine-American War. 

h4. See also

* [[list of weapons]] 
* [[Krag Jorgensen]] A Norwegian-designed bolt-action rifle with more ammunition capacity than the Trapdoor Springfields, that would officially replace it in 1892.
* [[Martini-henry ]] The British counterpart to the Trapdoor Springfield, as an single-shot rifle.

title: dshk
body:
Pronounced "Dushka". A [[Soviet]] 12.7×108 mm [b][[heavy machine gun]][/b] with a with a V-shaped butterfly trigger. It is mostly known for its use during [[World War II]], the [[Vietnam War]], as well as other [[war|armed conflicts]]. The [[weapon]] takes its name from its two designers, Vasily [b]D[/b]egtyaryov and Georgi [b]Sh[/b]pagin, with the [b]K[/b] standing for [b]Крупнокалиберный[/b] ([i]Krupnokaliberny[/i], "large-caliber").

h1. See also
* [[List of weapons]]
* [[kord 6p50|Kord]]
* [[NSV]]
* [[Browning M2]] The equivalent 12.7mm/.50-caliber machine gun produced by the United States. 

h1. External links
* "Wikipedia: DShK":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DShK

title: browning_m2
body:
The M2 Browning .50-caliber Machine Gun is a [[heavy machine gun]] designed by [[John Moses Browning]] near the end of the First World War.  It entered official US Military service in 1933 and is still actively used today, making it the second longest-serving weapon in the US Military after the [[M1911]] pistol.

Though the M2 can be carried by infantry and set up and used on the ground with a [[tripod]], it is most commonly seen as a [[manually-operated mounted gun]] on vehicles, tanks, and ships. It has also historically served as the primary weapon for [[aircraft turret]]s on American bombers such as the [[B-17 Flying Fortress]]. M2 and faster-firing M3 Browning machine guns were also the primary armament of American warplanes during [[World War II]] and the [[Korean War]], with loadouts of four, six, or even eight .50 caliber guns. 

The M2 Browning continues to be actively produced today, and is a standard weapon for the United States and many other nations. 

h4. See also

* [[List of Weapons]]
* [[M2HB (Girls' Frontline)]] 
* [[DShK]] The equivalent 12.7mm heavy machine gun design from the Soviet Union, also still in use today, though no longer produced. 

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: M2 Browning":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M2_Browning
other_names: ブローニングM2重機関銃

title: m1_carbine
body:
An American semi-automatic [[rifle|carbine]], chambered for the proprietary .30 Carbine [[ammunition|cartridge]]. Despite the name, it is not the shortened variant of the [[M1 Garand]] but instead its own distinct design. Adopted in 1942, the M1 Carbine was a standard [[gun|firearm]] for the US military during World War II, the Korean War and into the Vietnam War. Although the Carbine was the most-produced US small arm of WW2, it is a relatively rare sight in media, particularly in comparison to the far-less-common [[Thompson submachine gun]]. 

Distinguishing features of the Carbine are the two pins on the upper stock just forward of the bolt. World War Two-era Carbines had a clean barrel from the stock to the muzzle and simple flip-tab rear sights, though later versions added a [[bayonet]] lug and more advanced graduated rear sights. The standard feed system is a 15-round box [[magazine (weapon)|magazine]].

* The M1A1 Carbine is the variant that features a metal side-[[folding stock]] and a pistol grip.
* The [[M2 Carbine]] is the name given to Carbines made capable of firing on full-automatic. It is distinguished from the M1 in media through the use of the curved 30-round magazine instead of the 15-round box.
* The M3 Carbine is an M2 with a prototype night-vision scope attached to the top. 

h1. See also

title: submachine_gun
body:
A [b]submachine gun[/b] or SMG is a carbine-length, pistol-caliber [[gun|firearm]] that is capable of fully automatic fire. Early SMGs such as the [[MP18]] have rifle-like appearance. While more modern models do have features like [[folding stock]], pistol grip and a fire selector. The term "submachine gun" was coined by [[Thompson submachine gun|John T. Thompson]], to describe its design concept as an automatic [[weapon]] with notably less firepower than a [[machine gun]] (hence the prefix "sub-"). 

A subset of submachine gun is dubbed [b]machine pistol[/b], which are often used to describe a handgun with automatic fire capability (e.g. Glock 18C), or compact SMGs with [[handgun]]-like ergonomics (e.g. Micro Uzi).

title: rifle
body:
A long [[gun|firearm]] designed to be [[firing|fired]] from the shoulder, with a barrel that has a helical pattern of grooves ("rifling") cut into the barrel walls. The [[rifling]] causes the speeding [[bullet]] to spin, giving it more stability and penetrating power.

This tag also applies to a [b]carbine[/b], which is basically the shorter variant of a rifle.

title: secretive_plotter
body:
An alternate persona of [spoiler][[Yoo Joonghyuk]][/spoiler] in [[Omniscient Reader's Viewpoint]].

He is depicted with short black hair, similar to a medium curtain cut. He has multiple scars on his body, including one across the eye, one cross scar on the face, and several miscellaneous scars everywhere else. He wears a large black cloak that either has a starry sky print or turns him partially invisible (e.g. same color as the background). 

For tagging purposes, he also includes [spoiler]666, 999, 1863, etc. rounds of Joonghyuk[/spoiler] given that they're much more directly connected.

h4. See also:
* [[Yoo Joonghyuk]] 
* [[Oldest Dream]]

title: oldest_dream
body:
An alternate persona of [spoiler][[Kim Dokja]][/spoiler] in [[Omniscient Reader's Viewpoint]]. 

He is a younger boy depicted with short black hair similar to the typical Korean two-block haircut, a bandage on the face, a white collared shirt, a yellow/brown school vest, and black shorts. He has a pair of white socks and black shoes. There are several bandages on his knees and legs, though they are often not depicted.

title: kim_dokja
body:
The main protagonist of [[Omniscient Reader's Viewpoint]]. He has short black hair and frequently wears a white coat (Infinite Space Dimension Coat) on top of a collared black shirt. 

Kim Dokja can be distinguished from Yoo Joonghyuk in that his hair is a typical Korean two-block haircut. It's also a bit tidier and often has crossed bangs between the eyes. 

h4. See also:
* [[Oldest Dream]] 
* [[Yoo_Joonghyuk]]

title: yoo_joonghyuk
body:
Yoo Joonghyuk is co-protagonist in [[Omniscient Reader's Viewpoint]] and the original protagonist in Three Ways to Survive the Apocalypse.

He has short black hair with curtained hair bangs, distinguishable from Kim Dokja's in that it's closer to a medium curtain cut than the typical Koeran two-block. He's also described looking as a generic anime protagonist. He wears a black coat (Infinite Space Dimension Coat) and a black crew neck shirt with a silver collar and combat boots. 

His right eye will also glow yellow to indicate that an ability of his is being used.

h4. See also:
* [[Secretive Plotter]]
* [[Kim Dokja]]

He wears a [[brown shirt|brown]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[shirt]] with a [[brown vest]], a [[brown belt]] with a [[belt pouch|pouch]], [[brown pants]] and a pair of [[brown boots|brown]] [[lace-up boots]]. title: hephaestion_(fate)
body:
[[Lord El-Melloi II Case Files]] character. A Servant summoned by [[Doctor Heartless]]. She is considered to be [b]Iskandar's Shadow[/b], and is actually [[Hephaestion (true) (fate)|Hephaestion]]'s younger twin sister who worked as Iskandar's body double. Due to her lack of a proper name and identity, she is not seen as part of [[Ionioi Hetairoi (fate)|]]. She has subtle [[heterochromia]], with her left eye being [[blue eyes|blue]] and her right eye [[grey eyes|grey]], though it's not uncommon for both to be the [[no heterochromia|same color]] (usually blue) either due to artistic license or [[artistic error]]. When using her [[mystic eyes]], they turn [[orange eyes|orange]].

She was released in [[Fate/Grand Order]] as a Pretender-class Servant remembering all the events of her previous summoning as a Faker, going by the name Hephaestion. [spoiler]Her true name as a Pretender is revealed to actually be [b]Hephaestion [[Mnemosyne (fate)|]][/b].[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Sakamoto Mineji]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Taichi You]]

Goth is an [[old man]] with [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] and [[brown eyes]]. He wears a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[green tunic]], a [[brown belt]], [[brown pants]] and a pair of [[brown boots]].

title: gotelinde_(genshin_impact)
body:
An quest-exclusive NPC from [[Genshin Impact]], she is a [[nun]] in Mondstadt's Church of Favonius. She denies [[Venti (genshin impact)|]] from getting the Holy [[Lyre]] der Himmel as she doesn't believe he is actually [[Barbatos (genshin impact)|]].

Gotelinde has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] tied into [[short twintails]], [[swept bangs]] and [[blue eyes]]. She wears the standard Church of Favonius nun uniform, consisting of a [[white dress|white]] and [[blue dress]] with [[juliet sleeves]], a [[white hat]] with a [[latin cross]] on it, a [[white veil]], [[white pantyhose]] and a pair of [[white shoes|white]] [[high heels]].

title: kujaku_(one_piece)
body:
[[One Piece]] character.

A Marine Rear Admiral and Granddaughter of [[tsuru_(one_piece)|Tsuru]]

She has [[long_hair|long]] strawberry [[blonde_hair|blonde hair]], [[green_eyes|green eyes]] and [[thick_lips|plump lips]]. For the Marine uniform she wears a [[strapless_dress|strapless pink dress]] and the [[coat_on_shoulders|marine coat]] draped over it. On her head she wears a [[cloche_hat|cloche hat]], with a printed M and a [[bird_hat_ornament|seagull accessory]].

title: sky_(nikke)
body:
A character from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. She is the leader of [[Over the Horizon (nikke)|]], the Ark's aeronautical squad which consists of her, [[Cielo (nikke)|]] and [[Sora (Nikke)|]].

Sky is the leader and [[pilot]] for the squad. She is normally calm and level-headed, though she can get overly excited when in flight. She is also a fan of [[rock (music)|rock and roll]] music.

Sky has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]], [[parted bangs]] and [[brown eyes]]. She wears a [[cropped shirt|cropped]] [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]] showing her [[stomach]], a [[yellow neckerchief]], a [[black coat]] [[coat on shoulders|on her shoulders]] with her [[id card]] on the left [[lapels|lapel]], [[white shorts|white]] [[short shorts]], [[white thighhighs]] and a pair of [[white shoes|white]] [[platform shoes]]. She has a [[blue hairband]] with a [[white bow|white]] [[hair bow]] in her hair and a [[thigh holster]] on her left leg.

h4. External links

* "Nikkepedia: Sky":https://nikke-goddess-of-victory-international.fandom.com/wiki/Sky

title: kei_(blue_archive)
body:
A character from [[Blue Archive]]. Depicted as being visually identical to [[Aris (blue archive)|]], with the difference being the [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[pink eyes]] and, sometimes, the [[red halo]].

[spoilers]She is another personality that resides within [[Aris (blue archive)|]]' mind, and is the representation of her original programming to carry out a genocidal campaign in the name of the "Nameless Priests" who created her. She will often refer to Aris as "Princess" in reference to this role. Originally she was referred to as <Key> as the program meant to unlock Aris' nature as the Princess of the Nameless Priests, but would be given the name of "Kei" during the events of Volume F as Aris accepted her as a part of her existence.[/spoilers]

Due to her nature, fanart typically portrays her as having a more caustic or aggressive personality compared to the normally kind and curious Aris.

[spoilers] In Decagrammaton Chapter 2 "Sword of Flames" Kei has been revived and her consciousness was loaded onto a purpose-built AMAS robot produced by [[rio_(blue_archive)|Rio]].

In the upcoming chapter "Sky of Unity" and the 6th PV, Kei managed to integrate a body similar that of Decagrammaton, her purpose for it is unknown at the moment. [/spoiler]

h4. Appearance

* !post #5849411: Original
* !asset #22540813: [[Kei (Robot) (blue archive)|Robot]]
* !asset #25862425: [[Kei (AMAS) (blue archive)|AMAS]]
* !post #9272483: [[Kei (new body) (blue archive)|New Body]]
other_names: ケイ(ブルーアーカイブ)

title: emotionless_sex
body:
When one or more characters involved in a sex act show [[bored|boredom]], disinterest, or [[expressionless|no emotion at all]].

Common signs are a deadpan expression, lack of blushing, or the character on the receiving end [[multitasking]] by doing other activities like [[reading]] or [[playing games]] at the same time.

Don't confuse this with [[empty eyes]].

h4. See also

* {{pool:Awkward_Sex}}
* [[expressionless]]

title: gumina_glassred
body:
Gumina Glassred was an aristocrat of the Beelzenian Empire residing in Asmodean and one of [[Sateriasis Venomania]] 's many victims. A childhood friend of Cherubim and his brother, Gumina grew opposed to her betrothal to Sateriasis. Scorning Cherubim to avoid his brother murdering him, Gumina was later enchanted and abducted by the Duke, becoming the sixth member of his [[harem]].

Portrayed by [[GUMI]]. Her given song is [[glassred no shouzou (vocaloid)|Glassred no Shouzou]]

h4. See Also
* [[List of Evillious Nendaiki characters]]

title: meikai_no_nushi
body:
[b]Master of the Hellish Yard[/b] 

A mysterious masked woman appearing before [[Gallerian Marlon]] at the end of [[Akutoku no Judgement (vocaloid)|]] and briefly joining the chorus of [[Chaban Capriccio (vocaloid)|]]. Determines who goes to heaven or hell, and believed to be in possession of [[Grim the End]] by [[Ma (evillious nendaiki)|]]. She is represented by [[GUMI]].

[spoiler]Her true identity is [[Gumillia]], who while alive was unable to leave the Hellish Yard after the events of the Battle of Merrigod Plateau.[/spoiler]

title: hakaba_no_aruji
body:
[b]Master of the Graveyard[/b]

A [[Banica Conchita]] [[look-alike]] who appears in [[Heartbeat Clocktower (vocaloid)|]] as the awakened [[Glass of Conchita]] and the new [[Master of the Graveyard (vocaloid)|]]. She reappears as a minor character in [[Twiright Prank (vocaloid)|]] and a major one in [[Chaban Capriccio (vocaloid)|]].

[spoiler]Turns out to [i]actually[/i] be Banica Conchita as the new demon of gluttony. She is utilized by [[Abyss I.R.]] during [[Aku no Musume (series)|]] to try and disrupt the legitimacy of the Lucifenian royal family, with the instruction being to possess the heir [[Allen Avadonia|Alexiel Lucifen d'Autriche]]. However, because he offered her his snack, she instead decides to possess his twin sister [[Riliane Lucifen d'Autriche|Riliane]]. The resulting chaos ends with Riliane losing her memories after being exorcised and Alexiel leaving the royal family, instead being taken in by the swordsman [[Leonhart Avadonia]] as [[Allen Avadonia]].[/spoiler]

h4. See Also
* [[List of Evillious Nendaiki characters]]

title: houtei_no_nushi
body:
[b]Master of the Court[/b]

A character from the Evillious Nendaiki portrayed by [[Hatsune Miku]]. The Master of the Court and the awakened form of the [[Clockworker's Doll]]. She's the director of [i]Evil's Theater[/i] and believes herself to be [[Michelle Marlon]] [spoilers]but is actually a reincarnation of [[Maria Moonlit]]/[[Irina Clockworker]].[/spoilers]

After the death of her "father", [[Gallerian Marlon]], she inherited his title, his task  and his dream, seeking to fulfill his wish by recollecting the [[vessel of sin|Vessels of Sin]] while she jugdes any intruder who dares to enter the Theater seeking the judge's fortune.

She's the main character of the songs [[Hakoniwa no Shoujo (vocaloid)|]], [[master of the court (vocaloid)|]], and [[Aku no Inga wa Owaranai (vocaloid)|]] and is featured in [[Chaban Capriccio (vocaloid)|]].

title: fumi_(jojolion)
body:
[spoilers] Joseph Joestar (仗世文ジョセフ・ジョースター, Josefu Jōsutā), also known as [/spoilers] Fumi (文), is a tertiary character featured in the eighth part of the [[JoJo no Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[JoJolion]].

Fumi is a teenager of above average height with an impressive physique, as noted by [[Lucy Steel|Lucy]]. He has short light hair styled in a [[buzz cut]] with three small spheres in the center. Under the spheres, two strands of hair stick out over his forehead, with one strand being longer than the other.

He wears a cashmere V-neck [[sweater]] with a striped collar. On the left of his sweater is a symbol of a large horseshoe framing an image of the dark silhouette of a rearing horse's head, similar to [[Johnny Joestar]]'s hat. He also has a collared long sleeve shirt underneath his sweater, with buttons beside the collars. Joseph wears baggy shorts with a waist bag on each side and geta sandals. The Japanese spelling of his name is carved on his geta.

[Spoilers]Fumi inherits the [[joestar birthmark|Star Birthmark]] on the back of his shoulder.[/spoilers]

title: irisu_shoukougun!
body:
English name: Irisu Syndrome!

A free puzzle videogame starring [[Irisu Kyouko]] and her friends, [[age hatori|Agetha]], [[edogawa takeru|Edogawa]], and [[uujishima satoshi (irisu)|Uuji]], a group of university students.

[spoiler]Based on how you play, you will either get a [[Bad End]]ing, which leads to death of the 3 university students.  Or a [[Good End]]ing where it is just a scary surprise party.  Or a perfect ending (in Metsu) where Irisu becomes sane, Uuji starts down the path to sanity as well, and all 4 of them -- Irisu, [[age hatori|Agetha]], [[edogawa takeru|Edogawa]], and [[uujishima satoshi (irisu)|Uuji]] are all friends.[/spoiler]

In February 2010 an expansion called いりす症候群！滅 (Irisu syndrome! Metsu -- aka Irisu Syndrome!  DESTRUCTION) was released, with hints of a 2nd expansion in the works. Though so far there are no further works from the series.

h4. External links

* "Download link":http://www.vector.co.jp/soft/win95/game/se463417.html
* "Game's website":http://members.jcom.home.ne.jp/wtetsu/index.html

title: chiffon_shirt
body:
A shirt made from chiffon, a lightweight, thin, and semi-transparent [[fabric]] . Its soft, flowing texture is often used to create an elegant and feminine appearance.

It is typically made in the form of a [[blouse]] , but can also be applied to various designs such as [[dress shirt]] or [[casual]] shirts. Due to the [[see-through shirt|material's sheer properties]], it is often worn with innerwear underneath.

title: japan_world_cup
body:
A fictional horse race [[3D]] CG video series held by The [[Japan Racing Association]] since 2010. The videos were created by "Mashima Riichirou":[http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=57284] and "Jinni's Animation Studio":[https://anidb.net/perl-bin/animedb.pl?show=creator&creatorid=22091].

The race itself is presented as a 1600m G1 race on turf held in Tokyo Racecourse (the race is identical in specifications to the [[Yasuda Kinen]]). It features a colorful cast of horses and non-horses racing each other in a extremely chaotic fashion. The result of the race is random with all outcomes being recorded in the DVD. This means that even perennial underdog Haribote Elegy has a chance to win.

h4. Characters

h5. Recurring

* [[Ginshari Boy]] (All) (Originally the most normal runner, he now has a tendency to dance on the racetrack.)
* [[Pink Pheromone]] (1,2) (French mare decked out in lingerie.)
* [[Chokuzen Bancho]] (All) (A delinquent horse, complete with pompadour and handlebars.)
* [[Hollywood Limousine]] (1,2) (American horse with overly long body, ridden by two jockeys, who can stretch his body even further.)
* [[Haribote Elegy]] (2.0, 3.0) (All) (A papier mâché "horse".)

h5. JAPAN WORLD CUP 1

* Burning Beef (A bull.)
* Savanna Stripes (A zebra.)
* Giraffe (Exactly what it is.)

h5. JAPAN WORLD CUP 2

* Konkon (A panda.)
* P.P. Donuts (A pony ridden by a toddler.)
* Jumbo Nam Pla (An asian elephant.)

h5. JAPAN WORLD CUP 3

* Super Pheromone (A mashup of Pink Pheromone with Hollywood Limousine's gimmick.)
* Ninja Sniper (A russian ninja horse.)
* Seaworld (A seal.)
* Trojan Horse ([[trojan horse|Exactly what it sounds]].)
* UMA (A [[yeti (creature)|]].)
* Mecha Haribote (A robotic version of Haribote Elegy.)

h4. External links

* "Official website":[http://www.jra-jwc.jp/]
* "Wikipedia (JP): Cinema Keiba / Japan World Cup":[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/CINEMA_KEIBA/JAPAN_WORLD_CUP]

title: dan_heng_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Itou Kent]]. 

The cold and reserved train guard of the [[Astral Express (honkai: star rail)|]]. Wielding a spear named Cloud Piercer, he joined the Astral Express crew to escape his secluded past. He is portrayed with [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] and [[green eyes]]. 

h4. Playable variations

* !post #7689858: [[Dan Heng (Hunt) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Default]] (Hunt)
* !post #7691302: [[Dan Heng (Imbibitor Lunae) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Imbibitor Lunae]] (Destruction)
* !post #9750485: [[Dan Heng (Permansor Terrae) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Permansor Terrae]] (Preservation)

h4. Non-playable costumes

* !post #7060430: [[Dan Heng (Beta Design) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Beta design]]
* !post #6727976: [[Dan Heng (Feast) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Feast]]
* !post #6601891: [[Dan Heng (KFC) (Honkai: Star Rail)|2023 KFC Collaboration]]
* !post #6284786: [[Dan Heng (Next Stop Yi County) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Yi County Collaboration]]

h4. Profile

[expand]
A cold and reserved young man who wields a spear known as Cloud-Piercer. He acts as the train's guard on its long Trailblaze journey.

He carefully observes the changes in everything around him, albeit with a calm demeanor that may appear to be indifference. He faithfully records everything they encounter on the Trailblaze path in the Express's archives.

Dan Heng never talks much about his past. In fact, he joined the crew of the Express to escape from it.

But will the Express really be able to take him far away from his past?
[/expand]

h4. See Also

* [[Dan Heng (Rice Dumpling) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Ruan Mei's creation: Rice Dumpling]]

title: science_adventure
body:
A multimedia franchise consisting of interconnected science fiction stories created by [[5pb.]], initially in collaboration with [[Nitroplus]]. The main entries mostly take the form of visual novel video games.

The series consists of six mainline entries: [[Chaos;Head]], followed by [[Steins;Gate]], [[Robotics;Notes]], [[Chaos;Child]], [[Occultic;Nine]], [[Anonymous;Code]]. The series also includes several spin-off videogames, anime, manga, light novels, audio dramas, and stage plays. All main entries except [[Anonymous;Code]] have received anime adaptations.

title: implied_self-harm
body:
When a picture strongly suggests someone has committed or may commit [b]intentional[/b] [[self-harm]] without depicting the act itself, the wounds caused, or [b][[blood]] at all[/b].

A common way is to include a [[boxcutter]] in the scene somewhere, especially in locations where a boxcutter wouldn't normally be, such as a [[bathroom]]. Another is for a character to have unexplained [[bandaged wrist]]s.

title: jewelry_bonney
body:
[[One Piece]] character. One of the [[Eleven Supernova]]s. "Big Eater" Jewelry Bonney is the captain of the Bonney Pirates. [spoiler]She is the adoptive daughter of [[Bartholomew Kuma]]. Her mother was [[Ginny (one piece)|]].[/spoiler]

Having consumed the Toshi Toshi no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], she has the power to alter peoples' physical age as well as her own. [spoiler]Her true age is revealed to be 12 years old in the Egghead arc.[/spoiler] She can also transform into a "what-if" version of herself, allowing her to copy the powers of other Devil Fruit users.

title: dick_gumshoe
body:
A detective in [[Ace Attorney]] who is [[Phoenix Wright]]'s friend and assists in solving cases. He has an obvious huge crush on [[Maggey Byrde]] but will not admit it. His English surname Gumshoe is a pun on 'gum on the shoe', meaning he is difficult to get rid of; additionally, both "Dick" and "Gumshoe" are slang words for a detective.

[b]Japanese name:[/b] Itonokogiri Keisuke (糸鋸 圭介 / いとのこぎり けいすけ)

Gumshoe has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] and [[black eyes]]. He has a [[stubble]], [[bandaid on face]] and a [[pencil]] behind his ear. He usually wears an [[orange necktie]] with a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[grey shirt|grey]] or [[brown shirt]]. He wears a [[long sleeves]] [[green coat]] on top and [[black pants]] with a [[black belt]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]] on his legs.

title: shadaloo_dolls
body:
The [b]Shadaloo Dolls[/b], or just the [b]Dolls[/b] for short, are a group of [[M. Bison]]'s [[mind control|brainwashed]] female underlings first introduced in [[Street Fighter Zero (series)|Street Fighter Zero III]], who serve as the co-sub-bosses in said game.

The initial twelve "Dolls" were young girls that Shadaloo has kidnapped from around the world to be brainwashed and re-conditioned as a specialist unit within the Shadaloo syndicate, with each named after the different months in their respective native tongue. The final Doll, [[Cammy White]], was specifically created from Bison's DNA and was to be a potential body replacement until she went rogue by the time of [[Street Fighter II (series)|]].

The Dolls can be distinguished by their uniform consisting of a [[striped clothes|striped]] [[blue leotard]] worn over a [[black pantyhose]], a [[beret]], [[red gloves]], [[yellow necktie]], and a [[boots]]. The exception of this is Cammy, who instead wear a light blue [[highleg leotard|highleg]], [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] leotard without a pantyhose, [[yellow gloves]], and boots.

This tag cover posts featuring characters wearing an outfit based on the Dolls, which may vary in color aside from canonical source. If the said leotard is based on a particular unique design (such as Cammy's), then the [[cosplay]] tag is applicable.

h4. Members

title: seabook_arno
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]Seabook Arno[/b] is the main protagonist of [[Gundam F91]], and childhood friend of [[Cecily Fairchild]]. During an incursion of his native colony by the vile [[Crossbone Vanguard]], he takes up arms in the cutting-edge [[F91 Gundam]] to fend off the insurgent pirates. 

[spoiler]After the Cosmo Babylonia Uprising, Seabook chooses to join forces with Cecily, now using her birth name of Berah Ronah, and lead a reformed Crossbone Vanguard under the alias of [[Kincade Nau]], at the controls of the [[Crossbone Gundam X-1]] in the [[Crossbone Gundam]] manga series.[/spoiler]

title: crimson_viper
body:
Codename [b]Crimson Viper[/b] ([b]クリムゾン・ヴァイパー[/b]), also known as [b]Maya[/b] ([b]マヤ[/b]), is a character from [[Street Fighter]] debuting in [[Street Fighter IV (Series)|]]. Her name is commonly shortened to [b]C. Viper[/b].

In SF4, Viper is an American operative employed by S.I.N. (Shadaloo Intimidation Network), the weapons division of Shadaloo led by [[Seth (street fighter)|]], who worked her way up to become head of the "Battle Suit" Project. The Battle Suit itself appears as a business suit but is stealthily augmented with numerous hidden gadgets such as electrically charged metal knuckles and jets in the shoes, as well as augmenting the user's natural physical abilities. The final test of the Battle Suit was for Viper to wear it herself and enter the World Warrior tournament as a fighter. She had run-ins with [[Chun-Li]], [[Cammy White]], [[Han Juri]], and [[M. Bison]] during the tournament. In reality, Crimson Viper is a secret agent for the CIA (U.S. intelligence); she went undercover at S.I.N to acquire data from the BLECE Project, in addition to eliminating "[[seth (street fighter)|Number 15]]". Though she failed at both objectives (the BLECE data was deleted by Cammy, and Juri took credit for destroying Seth), Viper was able to get away and keep the Battle Suit for herself.

C. Viper returns in [[Street Fighter 6]], with a new look and new rendition of the Battle Suit. She appears as a lead researcher for SiRN, though whether she is still a CIA double agent is unknown.

h4. Appearance

* !post #536468: Street Fighter 4
* !post #9440060: Street Fighter 6

title: tabara_seiki
body:
Retired [[real life]] Japanese horse [[jockey]]. Famous for achieving multiple victories with [[Mayano Top Gun (racehorse)|]],  as well as [[Happy Progress (racehorse)|]] and [[Flower Park (racehorse)|]]. He has also ridden  [[Tokai Teio (racehorse)|]] to victory once in the [[Arima Kinen]].

After retirement he became a racehorse trainer, though sadly his license was revoked after getting into trouble for accidentally bringing a fruit knife in his check-in luggage at an airport (which also landed him in further trouble when searching revealed he had some recreational drugs).

Tabara is also a professional manga author starting back from his jockeying days. His latest work, [[Hou no Niwa]] (The Courtyard of Law) has also been adapted into a television drama. Additionally, Mr. Tabara is a semi-prolific magazine columnist and musician.

h4. External links

* "Youtube: Tokyo Sports Race Channel":[https://www.youtube.com/@tokyosportsmovie]

title: sprixie_princess
body:
A group of characters from the [[Mario (series)|Mario series]] that first appeared in [[Super Mario 3D World]]. They are the rulers of the Sprixie Kingdom and the [[Sprixie]]s, a race of [[fairy|fairies]] who play an important role in the story. The Green Sprixie Princess also appears as a playable character in [[Mario Tennis: Ultra Smash]].

The seven princesses are captured by [[Bowser]] in [[glass bottle]]s and each is guarded in one of the first seven worlds. After all seven are rescued, they build a [[rocket]] that allows the player to reach World Star. They appear as the damsels in distress rather than [[Princess Peach]], as [[Koizumi Yoshiaki]] decided to make her a playable character instead.

The Sprixie Princesses are depicted as small [[fairy|fairies]] with [[fairy wings|wings]], a [[crown]], [[white gloves]], and a colored [[dress]]. They each have a unique hairstyle and hair color to match their dress.

title: kinugasa_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the second of the two ships of the [i]Aoba[/i]-class cruisers.

She has [[grey_hair|grey]]-[[pink hair]] tied up in [[short twintails]] with a pair of [[hair tie]]s, and [[green eyes]] in [[tsurime]] style.  She wears a standard [[serafuku]] with a yellow [[necktie]], a [[belt]], and dark brown [[thighhighs]]. When under medium damage, it is revealed she wears a [[yellow bra]] and [[side-tie panties]]. In her [[kinugasa kai ni (kancolle)|Kai Ni]] form she has a [[one side up]] hairstyle instead of twintails.

Her [[machinery|combat gear]] includes twin-[[cannon]] [[ship turret|turret]]s in each hand, the left significantly taller than the right, as well as a third turret strapped to her left thigh.  Strapped to her back like a backpack is a miniature replica of the original ship's bridge, with a [[crane (machine)|]] hanging off the back.  

She is a stereotypical energetic high school girl, but like many of the energetic destroyers or cruisers, she is mostly known (if she is known at all) as [[Aoba (kancolle)|]]'s less-popular younger sister, and is generally only seen in Aoba's company.

title: shigure_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Shigure[/i]. Designed by [[Kujou Ichiso]], voiced by [[Tanibe Yumi]].

She has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[brown_hair|dark brown]]/[[black hair]] with an [[ahoge]] in a [[braid]] over her [[hair_over_shoulder|shoulder]] as well as [[blue eyes]]. Her default outfit is the [i]Shiratsuyu[/i]-class' [[school uniform]]: a [[black_serafuku|black]] [[serafuku]], [[black socks]], and brown [[loafers]].

Her [[rigging]] at base form consists of her 12.7 cm twin gun mount to her back and two 61 cm quad [[torpedo tubes]] on [[thigh strap]]s.

Because of her quiet tone of voice, somewhat sad eyes, extreme fondness when referring to [[Fusou (kancolle)|Fusou]] and [[Yamashiro (kancolle)|Yamashiro]], and provoking taunts when damaged, there's a fan theory floating around the internet that believes Shigure suffers from PTSD from being the sole survivor of the Nishimura Fleet after the Battle of Surigao Strait.

She was the protagonist of the second season of the [[Kantai Collection (anime)|Kantai Collection anime]].

title: angel_(kof)
body:
Pronounced "An-hell" (as per the Spanish pronunciation of the word, therefore properly written as Ángel), a [[The King of Fighters|King of Fighters]] character who is well known for her striptease and killer physique, notably her [[large breasts|big breasts]] - tied with [[Shermie (kof)|]] for the biggest bust in all of KOF at 92 cm.

In [[The King of Fighters 2001]], Angel is introduced as an agent of the secret organization known as NESTS. A NESTS experiment herself, she is genetically augmented to have superhuman physical capabilities, including strength, agility, endurance and reflexes. She is assigned to keep an eye on the experiment [[K9999]], whose purpose is to hunt down traitorous experiments that had left NESTS. During the final moments of the tournament, it is revealed that both Angel and K9999 are actually on a mission to kill [[Kula Diamond]] and her guardians, but ultimately fail to do so. When NESTS ultimately falls, Angel escapes on her own and disappears.

In [[The King of Fighters XIV]], it is revealed that Angel abandoned NESTS entirely in its final moments and is now living for herself in her native [[Mexico]], though she is harrassed by NESTS agents for her betrayal. She still doesn't get along with Kula or the rest of Team K'. She forms a part of the new Team Mexico alongside [[Ramon (kof)|]] and the [[King of Dinosaurs|]].

In [[The King of Fighters XV]], Angel reunites with K9999 - now a fellow NESTS renegade under his new name [[Krohnen]] and with a slightly less volatile temperament - and teams up with him and a rebellious Kula to stick it to Team K'. After the tournament, Angel returns Kula to her guardians without a fuss and decides to travel with Krohnen for a while.

Angel's fighting style is self-described as "perfunctory," meaning she has no real training and makes up her style and strategy on the fly as she goes. This manifests as a combination of unorthodox speedy attacks and a small assortment of professional [[wrestling]] moves, particularly those inspired by [[the rock (dwayne johnson)|Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson]].

body:
An [[original]] character interacting with a canon character from a franchise, especially (though by no means exclusively) when romantically and/or sexually paired together. Especially prevalent with images with [[commissioner insert|commissioner]] or [[artist self-insert|artist]] inserted.

Custom playable characters from games such as the [[Mirai Senshi]] or [[Tav (baldur's gate)|]] count as original characters.

Unnamed or [[faceless]] characters don't count.

title: arima_miyako
body:
A character mentioned briefly in [[Tsukihime]] and [[Kagetsu Tooya]], but became more prominent in [[Melty Blood]]. 

She is the oldest daughter of the Arima family, a branch of the Tohno family [spoiler]with very weak [[oni]] blood[/spoiler]. She became the adoptive little sister of a nine year old [[Tohno Shiki]] after he was sent to live with her family. She idolizes Shiki immensely but is too shy to express herself clearly to him. In Melty Blood, she resents the Tohno family for taking Shiki from her and plans to take him back by force. While she knows some Bajiquan, the [[Night of wallachia|Night of Wallachia]] phenomenon enhances her martial art powers to incredible levels. 

She wears a [[red jacket|red]] [[tangzhuang]], [[denim shorts|denim]] [[short shorts]] with [[cutoffs]] and dark [[blue socks]] with [[brown footwear|brown shoes]]. She has [[green eyes]] and wears [[red bow|red]] [[hair bow|bows in her hair]]s. Her design in [[Melty Blood: Type Lumina]], which represents the [[Tsukihime (remake)|remake]] timeline, changes some things of her design. Her brown shoes became [[pink footwear|pink]] and her denim shorts are now [[black shorts|black]] [[bike shorts]]. Her blue socks and red bows in her hair also became black instead. 

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24287018: Melty Blood
* !post #71654: Older Miyako from [i]"Character Material"[/i]
* !post #8201252: Melty Blood: Type Lumina

title: melty_blood
body:
[b]Melty Blood[/b] is a Japanese doujin 2D fighting game, developed primarily by [[Type-Moon]], [[French-Bread]] (known as [i]Watanabe Seisakusho[/i] prior to 2003), and Ecole. Yet another sequel of sorts to [[Tsukihime]].

It has also been adapted into a manga series, featuring art by Takeru Kirishima and serialized in the CompAce magazine, published 2005.

h4. Characters

As of Melty Blood: Actress Again, there are 25 playable characters.

body:
A [[Melty Blood]] character. A [[demon girl|succubus]] with a [[cat]] form like her counterpart [[Len (tsukihime)|]], she is also her polar opposite in personality and appearance. 

She is the familiar of [[Aozaki Aoko]], [spoiler]who created her out of the remains of [[Night of wallachia]] after his death.[/spoiler] 

Within the [[M.U.G.E.N]] fanbase, she is popularly paired with [[The King of Fighters]] character [[K' (kof)|]].

title: kishima_kouma
body:
A character in [[Kagetsu Tooya]] and [[Melty Blood]]. 

He is the eldest son of the Kishima family, a branch of the Tohno family facing extinction and harboring extremely strong [[oni]] blood, rendering him more nonhuman than human. He wields immense herculean power and has scorching [[fire|flames]]. He was ordered by [spoiler]Tohno Makihisa[/spoiler] to be an accessory to the annihilation of the Nanaya clan, resulting in a decisive battle against [[Nanaya Kiri]], killing him in the process.

He is a [[muscular_male|muscular man]] with [[black eyes]], dark [[blue_hair|blue]] or [[black hair]] and [[hair over one eye]]. He wears [[fingerless gloves|fingerless]] [[black gloves]], [[black pants]] with [[toeless legwear]] underneath and a [[chinese clothes|chinese]] [[sleeveless_shirt|sleeveless]] [[black shirt]]. And he sometimes has on a [[fur-trimmed_coat|fur trimmed]] [[white coat]].

Despite still being alive and living in seclusion away from humanity, in the Melty Blood series another version of him still manifests as a [[night of wallachia|TATARI]], with little self awareness.

h4. Official art
* !post #8194469

title: nrvnqsr_chaos
body:
[tn][i]Pronounced "Nero" chaos[/i][/tn]

A character in [[Tsukihime]] and [[Melty Blood]]. One of the oldest of the 27 Dead Apostles Ancestors and one of the most exceptional. 

He is an accumulated chaotic mass of 666 beasts that swirl within him, and he unleashes these beasts to devour his victims blood, meat and bones whole. He plans to swallow [[Arcueid Brunestud]] in order to claim unrivaled power among the highest rank of vampires and is an old friend of [[Michael Roa Valdamjong]]. In the Melty Blood series he is a reoccurring manifestation of [[night of wallachia|TATARI]].

He has [[grey hair]], [[grey eyes]] and his face has [[pale skin]]. He wears a [[blue_coat|blue]]/[[black_coat|black]] [[trench coat]] and most of his body below his neck is the total [[black_skin|blackness]] of chaos. 

Before becoming a vampire his human name was [b]Fabro Rowan[/b], who appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. In the [[Tsukihime (remake)|Tsukihime Remake]] his role in the story was replaced by [[Vlov Arkhangel]].

h4. Official art

title: tokoyami_towa_(cyberpunk)
body:
The 5th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Tokoyami Towa]], as seen on "Twitter":[https://twitter.com/MegaJujube/status/1681639565243858945] and released on July 19, 2023.

It consists of a [[white tube top]], a [[white shrug|white]] [[turtleneck]] [[hooded shrug|hood]] with a [[demon hood|demon]], a [[chest belt]], [[puffy long sleeves|long, puffy]] [[see-through sleeves]], a pair of [[ski goggles]] [[goggles on head|on her head]], [[white shorts|white]] [[short shorts]] with [[multiple belts]], a [[thigh pouch]] held with a pair of [[thigh strap|straps]], differently-colored [[knee pads]] (purple on her left, green on right), multiple [[bandaid on leg|bandaids]] on her legs, [[grey socks|grey]] [[loose socks]] and [[white boots|white]] [[roller skates]]. She also has solid [[white wings|white]] [[demon wings]], her [[winged heart tattoo|winged heart]] [[tattoo]] is now on her [[hip tattoo|right hip]] instead of her thigh and has a [[megaphone]] as an optional accessory.

She has 2 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] in this costume:
* [[Very long hair|Very long]] [[pink hair]] with [[white hair|white]] [[streaked hair|streaks]] done in a [[high ponytail]]
* [[Low twintails|Low]] [[low twin braids|twin braids]] from her [[tokoyami towa (underworld uniform)|underworld uniform costume]]

title: silvervale
body:
An English-speaking [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]]. Originally an [[indie virtual youtuber|indie]], she later became one of the founding members of [[VShojo]], until leaving to return being an indie on April 26, 2023. She is the (non-IRL) significant other to VShojo virtual YouTuber [[Vei (vtuber)|]], having married to each other in [[Final Fantasy XIV]] in February 2021.

Being a [[wolf girl]] she naturally has [[wolf ears]] (although she sometimes wears [[animal ear headphones|wolf ear headphones]]), a [[pink tail|pink]] and [[blue tail|blue]] [[wolf tail]], [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair|pink]] and [[blue hair|blue]] [[gradient hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and [[blue eyes]].

title: ort_(type-moon)
body:
A major antagonist hinted at in [[TYPE-MOON]]'s earlier works like [[Tsukihime]], and eventually implemented into [[Fate/Grand Order]] as a story raid boss. ORT is an extraterrestrial being sent to Earth explicitly to destroy it, and is said to be so powerful that humanity cannot possibly defeat it with its own power. In [[Nahui Mictlan (fate/grand order)|]], [spoiler]it had its core ripped out by [[Camazotz (fate)|]], which eventually became [[Kukulkan (fate)|]]. When it reawakens during Chaldea's arrival, it absorbs the traits of the servants attacking it and is able to summon the Grand Foreigner servant version of itself, [[ORT Xibalba (fate)|]].[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[PFALZ]]

title: keikyoku_no_machi_wa_doko_e_(project_sekai)
body:
The 145th event of [[Project Sekai]]. The focus of this event is [[25-ji Nightcord de. (project sekai)|]]

Within the fandom, the event is often referred to as Mizu5, in reference to it being the fifth event featuring [[Akiyama Mizuki]] as a focus character. Became a "meme":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/mizu5], as Mizuki's shocked face in the event's featured card became a common reaction image following its posting by the Japanese [i]Project Sekai[/i] X account "teasing the event":[https://x.com/pj_sekai/status/1844574014326571513]. The event story's developments, which involved Mizuki being "apparently outed":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qdh3kHkj17g] to [[Shinonome Ena]] as having been born a boy by two of their schoolmates, sparked significant debate within the [i]Project Sekai[/i] fandom as to the question of Mizuki's gender identity (which remains not officially confirmed).

title: mold_(casting)
body:
A casting mold (also spelled [i]mould[/i]) is a hollowed-out container that is used to create specifically shaped object in the field of [[cooking]] and [[industrial]] crafts like metalworking and glass-making. By [[pouring]] the liquid or pliable material into the mold, the material will solidified into the desired object to be removed from the mold and further processed. 

For visible fungus associated with food spoilage, please use [[mold]] instead.

title: tokoyami_towa
body: A [[Virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] and member of [[hololive]]'s 4th generation, also called "[[holoForce]]". Designed by [[Rurudo]]. Towa is a [[demon girl]] with [[green eyes]], [[pointy ears]], a [[demon tail]] and [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] with [[pink hair|pink]] [[streaked hair|streaks]] and [[colored inner hair]] (with later costumes and revisions to her base model adding a pink [[gradient hair|gradient]] too), kept in [[twintails]] with [[double-parted bangs]] forming a [[center-flap bangs|flap]] [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]] and [[sidelocks]] with [[parallel hairclips]] on each side. She has multiple [[spike piercing|spike]] and hoop [[ear piercing]]s on both ears with also an [[earclip]] on her right ear and an [[industrial piercing]] on her left ear, she also has a [[navel piercing]] and even some [[tail piercing|piercings on her tail]]. She wears a [[black hat|black]] [[horned headwear|horned]] [[baseball cap]] with an OwO face, which is actually her pet and mascot [[Bibi (tokoyami towa)|]]. h4. Costumes h5. title: tokoyami_towa_(underworld_uniform)
body:
The 4th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Tokoyami Towa]], as seen in "Rurudo's official design link":[https://twitter.com/rurudo_/status/1550105403455053824] (ex. post #5565174).

It is a black [[school uniform]], consisting of a [[black jacket|black]] [[cropped jacket|cropped]] [[blazer]] with [[sleeve cuffs]], a [[black shirt|black]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[dress shirt]] with a [[purple necktie|purple]] [[short necktie]], an [[underbust]] [[black corset]], a [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]] with a solid black front and [[plaid skirt|plaid]] sides, [[black socks|black]] [[pinstripe socks]], and [[black footwear]] [[loafers]]. She now also has [[black horns|black]] [[demon horns]] and [[demon wings|wings]] to emphasize her "devilish" character.

She has 2 different [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyles]] in this costume:
* [[Long hair]] done in [[low twintails|low]] [[low twin braids|twin braids]]
* Long hair tied in a [[drill ponytail|drill]] [[side ponytail]]

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24481623: Profile

title: ookami_mio_(hoodie)
body:
The 3rd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Ookami Mio]]. It comes in two versions, one with a hoodie and another with a white shirt.

The hoodie version consists of a [[two-tone hoodie|two-tone]] [[black hoodie|black]] and [[white hoodie]] with a [[paw print pattern]] and [[sleeves past wrists|sleeves past her wrists]], a [[black choker]], [[black shorts|black]] [[ short shorts]] a [[black pantyhose]] and [[white shoes|white]] [[sneakers]].

The shirt version replaces the hoodie with a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt|white]] [[asymmetrical shirt]] with a [[shoulder cutout]] and the pantyhose with [[black socks]].

Originally, she used her regular hairstyle with this costume, but she later got the same [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[low twintails]] from her [[ookami mio (street)|5th costume]] as an option.

h4. Appearance

* !post #3724400: Profile (without hoodie)

title: shiranui_flare
body:
A [[Virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] and member of [[hololive]]'s 3rd generation hololive Fantasy.

She is a [[dark-skinned female|dark-skinned]] [[elf]] with [[pointy ears]], [[long hair|long]], [[streaked hair|streaked]] [[blonde hair]], often kept in a [[high ponytail]] held with a [[hair bow]] and [[long sidelocks]]. She also has [[large breasts]] that while she downplays them with most of her costumes, are actually larger than [[Houshou Marine|Marine]]'s.

title: miteiru_(shirakami_fubuki)
body:
A channel mascot of [[hololive]]'s [[Shirakami Fubuki]], originally introduced as a generic "stare" emote for her chat in October 2020, hence its name. Designed by Fubuki herself, as seen on "twitter":[https://twitter.com/shirakamifubuki/status/1315217059257622530]

It's depicted as a blob [[creature]] styled after a [[fox]] with [[solid eyes]] and wearing the same [[blue bowtie]] as [[shirakami fubuki (parade dress)|Fubuki's 6th outfit]], according to Fubuki it can stick to any surface, stretch into any shape and never blinks.

h4. Appearence
* !post #8692714: Original design

title: shirakami_fubuki_(parade_dress)
body:
The 6th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Shirakami Fubuki]], revealed on her 2020 birthday special.

Her aristocratic [[lolita fashion|lolita]] outfit is [[victorian]]/[[steampunk]]-inspired and consists of a dark [[blue jacket]] with [[sleeve cuffs]], a [[mini top hat]], [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]], a combination of a [[blue bowtie]] and an [[ascot]] an [[underbust]] [[black corset]], a [[grey skirt|grey]] knee-length [[frilled skirt]], [[white gloves]], and a [[white pantyhose]].

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[very long hair]] tied into a [[braided ponytail]] with a [[black hairband]].

body:
The 6th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Oozora Subaru]]. This costume is largely based on her [[Oozora subaru (suspenders)|2nd costume]] with an [[idol]] motif, it was revealed during her 4th anniversary 3D live in November 2022.

It consists of a [[white hat|white]] [[beret]] with a [[sunflower hair ornament]], an [[orange jacket|orange]] [[short-sleeved jacket|short-sleeved]] [[cropped jacket]] with a [[pinstripe jacket|pinstripe pattern]] with a [[white shirt|white]] [[frilled shirt]] with [[center frills]] underneath, 2 bowties on top of each other (a[[white bowtie|white]] [[striped bowtie|striped]] one and a [[black bowtie|black]] one under it) held with a [[flower brooch]], a [[grey corset|grey]] [[underbust]] [[corset]], [[white gloves|white]] [[frilled gloves]], [[black shorts]] with [[suspenders]] and a [[hip vent]] showing her [[orange panties]], a [[green sash]] with a [[floral bow|floral]] [[waist bow]], a [[layered skirt|layered]] [[overskirt]] with an outer [[orange skirt|orange]] [[vertical-striped skirt|vertical-striped]] [[pinstripe skirt]] and a [[white skirt|white]] [[frilled skirt]] underneath, a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[argyle thighhighs]] with [[white garter straps]] and [[black boots|black]] [[high heel boots]].

She has her usual [[short hair]] with [[swept bangs]] from her previous costumes and [[Long hair|long]] [[straight hair]] also with swept bangs as an [[official alternate hairstyle]]

title: oozora_subaru_(suspenders)
body:
The 2nd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Oozora Subaru]].

Her second costume consists of a [[grey hat|grey]] [[sailor hat]], a [[blue jacket|blue]] [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[cropped jacket]] with [[sleeve cuffs]], an [[armband]] and [[gold buttons|golden]] [[buttons]], a [[high collar|high-collared]] [[cropped shirt|cropped]] [[grey shirt|grey]] [[sleeveless shirt]] with a [[pinstripe shirt|pinstripe]] pattern, a [[black bowtie]] with a golden [[star brooch]], [[blue shorts]] with [[suspenders]] and a [[large bow|large]] [[back bow]] and [[hip vent]]s [[panty peek|showing the waistband]] of her [[lace-trimmed panties|lace-trimmed]] [[black panties]], [[grey thighhighs]], and [[black boots|black]] [[high heel boots]]. As this is the costume that Subaru uses for her "Oozora Police department" streams, it is also often drawn with a [[police hat]] instead of her sailor hat.

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this costume is [[short hair]] with [[swept bangs]] and a [[side braid]] held with a golden [[star hair ornament|star]] [[hairclip]].

title: hoshimachi_suisei_(sailor)
body:
The 4th [[official alternate costume|costume]] of [[hololive]]'s [[Hoshimachi Suisei]].

It's a [[school uniform]]-themed outift and comes in 2 versions:
* A [[white serafuku]] consisting of  a [[grey cardigan|grey]] [[aran sweater|aran cardigan]], a [[blue choker]], a [[white shirt]] with a [[white sailor collar]] with a [[white dress]] underneath, a [[blue bowtie]] and a [[blue belt]].
* A [[black serafuku]] consisting of a [[white jacket|white]] [[hooded jacket]] with [[cat hood|cat ears]], a [[black choker]], a [[black shirt]] with a [[black sailor collar]] with a [[black dress]] underneath, a [[yellow bowtie]] and a [[grey belt]].

In both versions the shirt has [[frilled sleeves|frilled]] [[puffy short sleeves]], a [[star brooch]] holding the bowtie, the dress is a [[pleated dress|pleated]] and [[medium dress|knee-length]], and both have [[white socks]] and [[black shoes|black]] [[loafers]], she also wears [[pearl earrings]] on both versions.

Her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] with this outfit is [[long hair]] in a [[half updo]] with a [[single side bun|single]] [[side up bun]].

title: georgia_(state)
body:
A state in the south-east region of the [[United States]], and one of the original thirteen colonies to form the nation after the [[American Revolution]]. Nicknamed "the [[Peach]] State", Georgia was one of the eleven states to secede from the Union to form the [[Confederate States of America]] in 1861, and during the ensuing [[American Civil War]] suffered severe damage, famously being the reluctant host of [[William Tecumseh Sherman|Sherman]]'s March to the Sea. 

The largest state by land mass fully East of the Mississippi River, Georgia's capital city [[Atlanta (city)|]] is both its largest city and most populous, with more than half of the state's total population living in the Atlanta metro area. 

Georgia is known for several sports teams and music groups, and is also the home of several large corporations like [[Coca-Cola]] and [[Delta Airlines]]. It has also in recent years made inroads in filming and movies, surpassing [[California]] in 2016 as the state with the most feature films produced on location.

Not to be confused with [[Georgia (country)]].
h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Georgia (U.S. state)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georgia_(U.S._state)]

title: miia_(monster_musume)
body:
Main heroine of [i][[Monster Musume No Iru Nichijou]][/i].

A [[lamia]] (snake girl) with [[long hair|long]] [[red hair]], [[yellow eyes]] with [[slit pupils]], [[pointy ears]], small [[scales]] on her cheeks and [[large breasts]]. Her most noticeable physical trait is her long, red [[snake]]-like lower body. She's often wearing 'D' [[hairclip]]s on each side of her head (from the front the clips resemble a snake's eyes while her hair acts as the [[fangs]]), which are part of her species' costume.

She is the first to be [[Kurusu Kimihito]]'s ward when the cultural exchange began. She is a sweet, naive and carefree individual, and has a habit of being clingy when she sleeps. She's very ticklish when one holds the very tip of her tail, which is why Kimihito exploits that weakness in order to get out of her grip. She always refers to him as "[b]Darling[/b] ([i]だぁりん Daarin[/i])", even when speaking to others about him.
other_names: ミーア(モンスター娘のいる日常)

title: fujinami_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Fujinami[/i]. Character design by [[Fujikawa]], voiced by [[Tanibe Yumi]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair|purple]]-[[grey hair]] tied in a [[side ponytail]] with [[asymmetrical bangs]] and an [[ahoge]]; and [[yellow eyes]]. Her default outfit is the [i]Yuugumo[/i]-class [[school uniform]]: a purple [[sleeveless dress]] over a [[white shirt]], a teal-blue [[bowtie]] and [[grey pantyhose|grey]] opaque [[pantyhose]] with [[lace-up boots]]. In her damaged art, she is shown to wear [[striped panties|striped]] [[side-tie panties]].

Her [[rigging]] consists of a [[smokestack|funnel]] and [[mast]] worn like a backpack with yellow straps, two 61 cm quad [[torpedo tubes]] on [[thigh strap]]s, and a handheld 12.7cm twin gun mount.

title: shantae
body:
Main character of the [[Shantae (Series)|]] series. A guardian half-genie whose job it is to protect Scuttle Town from danger, which is often pirate attacks from [[Risky Boots]]. Her main method of attack is her long hair which she uses as a whip and she performs various magical dances to transform into various [[alternate form|forms]].

Shantae is a [[belly dancing|belly]] [[dancer]] who usually dons a bedlah. Her attire consists of a red [[o-ring top]] with a matching pair of [[harem pants]] and [[red shoes|red]] [[pointy shoes]]. Gold [[jewelry]] has a significant role in her design with a [[hair ornament]] that gives her a [[high ponytail]], a pair of [[bracer]]s, [[hoop earrings]], and a [[circlet]]. She also wears a [[purple choker]] to match her [[very long hair|very long]] [[purple hair]].

[[Uncle Mimic|Mimic]] is her adopted uncle.

body:

Is a [[horse]]. Has a bay (i.e. brown) coat. Amago Vaccine is drawn with human-like masculine facial features. His most salient feature is the white "shadow roll" (a type of horse "blinkers" used to restrict vision to improve focus) worn across the noseband of his bridle.

title: jack_d'or_(racehorse)
body:
[tn]Given etmyology is "Person's name + French: 'Golden'."[/tn]

Japanese [[horse|racehorse]]. Sired by [[Maurice (racehorse)|]] (thus, his great-grandfather is [[Grass Wonder (racehorse)|]]) and foaled by [[Ravarino (racehorse)|]]. He is famed for his front-runner running style.

He is a chestnut horse with a wide blaze marking with stockings on all but his left front leg, which has a sock.

Something of a late bloomer, he came to prominence with his first title at the 2022 Kinko Sho, becoming the winner of a stacked 2022 Sapporo Kinen (defeating his front-runner sempai [[Panthalassa (racehorse)|]] and reigning champion [[Sodashi (racehorse)|]]) and winning his first G1 at the 2023 Osaka Hai.

title: grand_admiral_thrawn
body:
[b]Grand Admiral Thrawn[/b] is a fictional character in [[Star Wars]] created by Timothy Zahn. He originally appeared in the Star Wars Expanded Universe's novels, the Thrawn trilogy (1991), before he was made canon in the new [[Disney]] Star Wars' canon.

A Grand Admiral within the [[Galactic Empire (star Wars)|]], Thrawn is a [[Chiss]], a race of red eyed, blue skin aliens, which is unusual in the Empire since the Empire are pro-Human and discriminate against alien races. Yet despite that, Thrawn was not only accepted within the Empire but was able to rise to a high position within the Imperial Navy. 

A brilliant and very dangerous strategist who is well respected by his men, Thrawn commands the remants of the Galactic Empire, following their defeat with the Rebel Alliance.

In both the [[Star Wars Rebels]] cartoon and the live action series [[Star Wars: Ahsoka]], Thrawn is voiced and portrayed by Lars Mikkelsen.

h4. See also
* [[Paptimus Scirocco]] - A previous [[Gundam]] antagonist character with similar traits (and uniform).
