title: noah_(d.gray-man)
body:
Noahs or the Clan Of Noah are a Faction in the D.Gray-Man series

They are descendants of the survivors of the destruction of the previous world who repopulated the new world after the new world was formed. They serve as the main antagonists Faction in the D.Gray-Man series as they desire to destroy Innocence, and also destroy the new world and kill its people as revenge for the destruction of their world.

Members of this Faction are recognizable from normal humans with their grey/dark skin, the stigmata mark/stitches on their forehead and yellow eyes. However they can also assume the appearance of a normal human if they want to which allows them to blend among normal humans pretty easily. It is also revealed that any human has the potential to turn into a Noah since all humans possess the Noah gene due to them being descendants of the survivors of the destruction of the previous world

There can only be a total of 14 Noah at once. Each Noah also represents a certain concept associated with the Noah and humanity as a whole. When a Noah dies, they are later reincarnated in the body of a new human a while later after their previous death.

Members of the Clan Of Noah include:

. [[Millennium Earl]] / [spoiler][[Mana Walker]][/spoiler]
. [[Nea D Campbell]]

. [[Tyki Mikk]]

title: bangboo_20_(zenless_zone_zero)
body:
A [[Bangboo (zenless zone zero)|]] employed by [[Belle (zenless zone zero)|]] and [[Wise (zenless zone zero)|]]. Bangboo 20, also known as "Twentie", is visually identical to [[Eous (zenless zone zero)|]], except numbered 20 on their bandana instead of 01. Only use this tag if the "20" is clearly visible.

A former employee of the Phaethon siblings who left to find their own work before the events of the game, they were rehired to run the Waifei Peninsula branch of Random Play. They can normally be found operating the stall just outside of Siubian Temple.

title: bison_(arknights)
body:
[i]Messenger Bison is proof that stability does not always follow age.[/i]

A playable Defender Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: Bison Pides

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Lungmen[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]

      [td]163 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]1 year[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

A young but incredibly capable executive manager of MountainDash Logistics, which has close ties with Penguin Logistics. He now provides operational assistance to Rhodes Island during the contracted period between two companies.

He is the primary protagonist in the side story [i]Code of Brawl[/i].

His motif is based on bisons.

His [[voice actor]]s are [[Minagawa Junko]] (JP), Lu Xiaotong (CN) and Bae Jeong-mi (KR). His illustrator is [[Ryuuzaki Ichi]].

title: i-47_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese submarine I-47, nicknamed "Yona". Character design by [[Hoshiakari (C2 Kikan)|]]. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[low-tied long hair|low-tied]] [[black hair]] with long [[sidelocks]], and [[green eyes]]. Conspicuous on her damaged CG is a [[mole on ass|mole located on her right buttock]]. Her default outfit consists of a blue [[school swimsuit]] worn under a [[white shirt|white]] [[crop top]] with a [[white sailor collar]] and [[name tag]], [[grey neckerchief]], [[see-through skirt]], [[black thighhighs]], and [[grey footwear|grey]] [[ankle boots]]. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of her [[torpedo tubes]] to her back, [[headgear]] patterned off her real-life fins, and her 14 cm and 25 mm [[anti-aircraft gun]]s on [[thigh strap]]s. 

The historical submarine's only remarkable achievement was the sinking of USS [i]Mississinewa[/i] on November 11, 1944 using a [[Kaiten (weapon)|]] missile. She was later made a Kaiten mother ship at the end of 1944, decommissioned on November 30, 1945, and was sunk as a target off the Gotou Islands on April 1, 1946.

h4. Appearance

title: the_mist_(stephen_king)
body:
A 1980 [[science fiction]] psychological horror novel written by Stephen King. It follows protagonist David Drayton after his town is shrouded in a dense [[fog|mist]] that conceals otherworldy [[creature]]s. He takes refuge inside a [[supermarket]] where he must survive against not only creatures, but other survivors as well. Was later adapted into a movie in 2007 and a TV series in 2017.

body:
Olena is a 34 years old Ukrainian SU-24 pilot from the Carpathians, the west of [[Ukraine]].
Normally a motherly, honest to God woman, she has been suffering from the old sergeant's syndrome since [[russo-ukrainian war|2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine]] and fell into religious delusions.

Speaks with an accent. Dreams of having a family of her own.
She is the eldest of 4 siblings, one of them being [[Myroslava Bozhuk]], her only sister.

title: zack_fair
body:
A pivotal character in the backstory of [i][[Final Fantasy VII]][/i], referred to by other characters and seen numerous times in flashbacks. A member of SOLDIER, mentored by [[Angeal Hewley]], friend of [[Cloud Strife]], and romantic interest of [[Aerith Gainsborough]]. 

[spoilers]Being killed mere days before the chronological start of the game, in some ways he is the hero/protagonist [i]in absentia[/i] of FFVII. His death prompts Cloud to step into the void he leaves behind, in the process creating a false persona based on Zack to a large degree.[/spoilers] He finally gets his time in the spotlight in [i][[Crisis Core Final Fantasy VII]][/i]. [spoilers]And in the [i][[Final Fantasy VII Remake|FFVII Remake]] trilogy[/i] too.[/spoilers]

Voiced by Rick Gomez (CCFF7) and Caleb Pierce (FF7 Remake).

body:

A playable Guard Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: Djerwnapekhaper Saciut Hatshepsut

A renowned archaeologist and historian who work to uncover and preserve the history of Sargon.
The eldest daughter of the Hatshepsut royal family, and distant descendant of the [[lugalszargus_(arknights)|first Shahanshah]].
Now aiding Rhodes Island as a field operator.

First appeared as an NPC in the "Reclamation Algorithm" gamemode [i]Tales Within the Sand[/i], she later became a playable operator and the main character of the side story [i]Adventure That Cannot Wait for the Sun: Inudi Harek, Horakhet[/i].

Her motif is based on the Abyssinian [[cat]].

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Saitou Machiko]] (Japanese), Chen Tingting (Chinese), Sophia Eleni (English), and Seo Da-hye (Korean).
Her illustrator is [[Namie-kun]].

title: sephiroth
body:
The main antagonist of [[Final Fantasy VII]] and its spinoffs.

A former member of the Shinra Electric Company, commander of SOLDIER, and the primary antagonist of [[Final Fantasy VII]] and [[Final Fantasy VII Advent Children|Advent Children]], and featured in [[Before Crisis Final Fantasy VII|Before Crisis]], [[Crisis Core Final Fantasy VII|Crisis Core]], and [[Final Fantasy VII Ever Crisis|Ever Crisis]].

His remnants are [[Kadaj]], [[Yazoo]], and [[Loz]]. His theme song is the famed One-Winged Angel (overshadowing his original theme, Those Chosen by the Planet). Voiced by [[Morikawa Toshiyuki]] in Japanese and George Newbern in English.

For the concept of the Sephiroth in the Jewish Kabbalah, see [[Sefirot]].

title: song_dynasty
body:
The [b]Song[/b] (宋) dynasty was an [[Chinese Empire|imperial dynasty of China]] that ruled from 960 to 1279. The dynasty was founded by Emperor Taizu of Song, who usurped the throne of the Later Zhou dynasty and went on to conquer the rest of the Ten Kingdoms, ending the [[Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms]] period. The Song often came into conflict with the contemporaneous Liao, Western Xia and Jin dynasties in northern China. After retreating to southern China following attacks by the Jin dynasty, the Song was eventually conquered by the [[Mongolia|Mongol-led]] [[Yuan dynasty]], "controversially":[http://www.us8cn.net/ldquo23830236652004321518260802001322269rdquo.html#:~:text=%E2%80%9C%E5%B4%96%E5%B1%B1%E4%B9%8B%E5%90%8E%EF%BC%8C%E5%B7%B2%E6%97%A0%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E2%80%9D%20%E6%98%AF%E6%8C%87%E5%AE%8B%E4%BB%A3%E9%82%A3,%E7%A7%B0%E4%B8%BA%E2%80%9C%E5%BC%B1%E5%AE%8B%E2%80%9D%E3%80%82] seen by some as the end of Classical China.

h4. See also

A meticulous and attentive student of [[Kal'tsit (Arknights)|]] who officially became involved in field medical missions after a half-year of preparatory training. Unlike conventional medics, she actively looks for opportunities to attack the enemy through the use of various drug compounds.

One of the protagonists in the side story event [i]Twilight of Wolumonde[/i]. Very easily agitated and prone to shouting at others as shown in the side story and her multiple in-game lines. Also holds deep grudges against the Ursus Empire due to abhorrent living conditions she suffered under and deems them to be the ones responsible for the disappearance of her family.

Her motif is based on the [[mongoose]]. Her callsign is derived from [i]Folinic acid[/i], noted to be the first word she could not remember in a medical dictionary.

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Kondou Reina]] (JP) and [[Skyler Davenport]] (EN).

title: ozzy_osbourne
body:
[b]John Michael "Ozzy" Osbourne[/b] (3 December 1948 – 22 July 2025) was an English singer and songwriter, best known as the lead vocalist of the heavy metal band [[Black Sabbath]]. 

He became notorious for erratic behavior in the 1970s and 1980s due to extensive alcohol and drug use, which led to his divorce to Thelma Riley, his first wife and mother of their two children, Jessica and Louis, in 1972 and his firing from Black Sabbath in 1979. Since then, Osbourne has reunited with the band sporadically.

Post-Black Sabbath, Osbourne launched a successful solo career with hits like "Crazy Train" from [i]Blizzard of Ozz[/i] (1980), collaborating with guitarists Randy Rhoads and Zakk Wylde. He earned Grammy nods and sold millions of records, solidifying his "Prince of Darkness" persona.

In later life, Osbourne achieved renewed fame via [[MTV]]'s reality series [i]The Osbournes[/i] (2002-2005), which featured him, his second wife Sharon, and their children Jack and Kelly (their eldest daughter, Aimee, opted out to focus on her singing career).

17 days following Osbourne's final live performance with Black Sabbath and other metal rock bands at the Back to the Beginning concert, he passed away on the morning of 22 July 2025, at the age of 76. He was surrounded by his family at the time of his death.

h4. External Links
* "Wikipedia: Ozzy Osbourne":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ozzy_Osbourne]
* "Wikipedia: Black Sabbath":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Sabbath]

body:
A supporting character from the manga and anime [[One Piece]]. Bartolomeo "the cannibal" (this monicker is a reference to him loving to mock and   provoke people, as "eating people" is an Japanese idiom for "mocking people") is the captain of the Barto Club pirates.

Having consumed the Bari Bari no Mi [[Devil Fruit]], he has the power to create invisible energy barriers.

[spoiler]A massive fanboy obsessing over [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] in particular and the [[Straw Hat Pirates]] in general.[/spoiler]

title: suzuhara_lulu
body:
A former [[Nijisanji]] affiliated [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]]. She debuted on the same day as [[Yukishiro Mahiro]].

Due to some odd events (such as streaming ten hours of [[Ring Fit Adventure]] [i] immediately after[/i] streaming ten hours of [[Dark Souls I]]), Lulu gained a reputation for behaving like some sort of inhuman creature, a notion further developed by her habit of staring directly at the viewer when something doesn't go as it should and her weird remarks like implying her eyeballs can regenerate after being crushed, while claiming to be nothing but a normal college student.

She is part of the [[Saine Sisters]] trio along with [[Kamishiro Kurea]] and [[Sephira Su]], as the three virtual youtubers were designed by [[Saine]] and consider themselves sisters, sometimes appearing in each other channels.

Unexpectedly announced she would be graduating and ceasing activities on June 30, 2021.

title: watermark
body:
An image containing text or a [[logo]] superimposed on top of the image. Typically to identify the owner/creator of the work, prevent the image from being counterfeited and/or impede [[ai-generated|AI training]]. Some watermarks are also deliberately placed as a "paywall" on "samples" of "[[paid reward]]" images.

Posts with watermarks added by [[third-party watermark|third-parties]] (anyone other than the artist) should not be uploaded.

Add [[watermark grid]] if it spans over a majority/the whole image. Add [[too many watermarks]] if it's in excess as to be noticeable from the thumbnail.

h4. See also

* [[copyright notice]]
* [[logo]]
* [[sample watermark]]
* [[signature]]
* [[web address]]
* [[Tag group:Text]]
* [[third-party watermark]]

title: mast_(nikke)
body:
A character from [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]] and a member of the [[Aegis (nikke)|]] squad along with [[Helm (nikke)|]] and [[Anchor (nikke)|]].

Mast has longed to hit the high seas ever since she first saw the swashbuckling adventures portrayed in pirate films as a child. As time drew on, however, her soul-crushing tenure at the Naval Squad slowly made her disillusioned. Even so, her vibrant personality remains untarnished, and she always brightens everyone else's day aboard the ship she serves. She is often accompanied by a [[parrot]] named [[Morgan (nikke)|]].

She has [[purple eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[streaked hair|streaked]] [[black hair|black]]/[[pink hair]] tied in a [[twintails]] along with [[large breasts]]. Her outfit is a [[military uniform]] consisting of [[white shirt]] exposing her [[black bikini top]] with her [[white jacket]] with [[epaulettes]] are hanging on her shoulders, [[choker]], [[peaked cap]], [[black gloves]], [[white shorts]] and a pair of [[high heels]].

Illustrator: [[DFM (darknessdfm)|DarknessDFM]]

title: greyscale
body:
A completely colorless, black-and-white image. The image is composed exclusively of shades of black, white, and grey. It is very common for [[comic]]s and [[doujinshi]] to be in greyscale.

The image may have small highlights of color (known as [[spot color]]s), but the image as a whole should be predominately greyscale.

Don't use color tags like [[black eyes]] or [[black hair]] when tagging greyscale images. The exception is color background tags, so tagging [[white background]], [[grey background]], or [[black background]] is fine.

h4. Guidelines

* For completely colorless art, use [[greyscale]].
* For a post consisting of a single color that isn't grey, use [[monochrome]], not [[greyscale]].
* For a mostly greyscale post with a small amount of color as a highlight, use [[greyscale]] and [[spot color]].
* For a post using a mix of color and greyscale, use [[partially colored]], not [[greyscale]].
* For a colorless foreground and colorful background, use [[greyscale with colored background]], not [[greyscale]] or [[partially colored]].
* For a post that has solid black shadings, use [[greyscale]] and [[high contrast]].
* For posts with a small variety of colors but more than two actual colors, use [[limited palette]], not [[greyscale]] or [[monochrome]].

h4. Examples

* !post #5785450
* !post #5591560: [[Spot color]]

h4. Not greyscale

* !post #5653986: [[Monochrome]]
* !post #5761420: [[Sepia]]
* !post #5782023: [[Partially colored]]
* !post #6764762: [[Limited palette]]
* !post #3408688: [[Muted color]]

h4. See also

* [[greyscale with colored background]]
* [[high contrast]]
* [[lineart]]
* [[monochrome]]
* [[muted color]]
* [[partially colored]]
* [[sepia]]
* [[spot color]]

title: buzzy_beetle
body:
An enemy from the [[mario (series)|Mario]] series.

They are turtle-like enemies with a powerful shell that resists fire. Some Buzzy Beetles are capable of walking along walls or ceilings, and can drop from ceilings to ambush targets. Buzzy Beetles may have a spike on their shells - these are known as [[Spike Top]]s. Other Buzzy Beetles may have white wings granting them the ability to fly (making them [[Para-Beetle]]s).

Buzzy Beetles are quadripeds. Their legs and underside are yellow, and they typically have bright red or yellow eyes. Their shells are a solid color (typically blue or black, though Spike Tops may have a red shell instead) outside an alternate color on the shell's rim (typically white).

h4. Official art
* !asset #25533046

h4. See Also

* [[Spiny]]

title: spike_top
body:
A variant of the [[Buzzy Beetle]]. They have a red shell with a single [[spikes|spike]] on top, hurting anyone who tries to jump on them. They are extremely resilient due to even being unhurt by fireballs.

h4. See Also

* [[Spiny]]

title: triss_(wuthering_waves)
body:
Non-playable character in [[Wuthering Waves]].

A girl who was considered a little sister to [[Phrolova (Wuthering Waves)|]] as well as a strong supporter of her musical ventures. She died upon a meteorite striking their home village leaving Phrolova as the only survivor, the latter of who now seeks to revive Triss as well as the rest of her village's people.

Triss' form is currently used by the Grand Architect, a Fractsidus Overseer suggested to be the overall leader, to appear before Phrolova, both to recruit her and make sure that her personal endeavours do not conflict with the Fractsidus' goals.

title: pangya
body:
An online multiplayer [[golf]] game series. The original game was launched in South Korea in 2004, North America and Japan in 2005, and Thailand in 2007. Only the Thai version of the original game remains online as of 2020, with the Korean and North American servers having closed in 2016 and in Japan in 2017.

Tomy released a single player version, [b]Pangya: Fantasy Golf[/b], in 2009.

The iOS and Android successor title [b]Pangya Mobile[/b] was launched in all four regions in 2017, before closing in 2020. A revised version, [b]Pangya M[/b], was launched on July 3, 2020 for mobile devices alongside a PC version on the NCSoft Purple platform.

body:
[i]Ceylon, researcher of Rhodes Island, will provide you with knowledge and technical support on Originium in her spare time.[/i]

A playable Medic Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: Ceylon Doykos

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]

The daughter of the Siesta mayor and a graduate of the Victorian National University who majored in Originium Research. She joins Rhodes Island along with Schwarz as an assistant researcher to [[Kal'tsit (Arknights)|]] on her indoor research work. She has a precocious level of mastery in water arts and can provide reliable treatment to allies on the battlefield.

Together with [[Schwarz (Arknights)|]], she is a supporting character in the side story [i]Heart of Surging Flames ~ Obsidian Festival[/i].

Her motif is based on a blue jay. Her given name and callsign comes from the old English name of [i]Sri Lanka[/i] which is famous for its tea production.

Her [[voice actor]] is [[Arakawa Miho]].

title: rash_guard
body:
A Rash Guard (sometimes called a [i]Rash Vest[/i], [i]Rashie[/i] or [i]Swim Shirt[/i]) is a type of athletic shirt worn for extra function and protection when surfing, snorkeling, jet skiing, or doing other watersports where you want more protection than a [[swimsuit]], but don't really need a full [[wetsuit]].  Most rash guards have long sleeves and while some women's tops show midriff, most are regular shirt length.  Of note, they are sometimes worn under a wetsuit or [[diving suit]] for added comfort.

Because rash guards are made from [[tight clothes]]-fitting materials like spandex, nylon, polyester, or neoprene and are often sold as matching top/bottom sets, this can sometimes make them appear similar to a [[wetsuit]] or [[one-piece swimsuit]] at a glance when no midriff is visible.  A clue to watch for is the horizontal line where the top-piece and bottom-piece come together/overlap.  If there is no line clearly identifying top from bottom, assume the garment is a wetsuit instead.

h4. Examples

* !post #2440870: long sleeve
* !post #1908423: short sleeve
* !post #6471525: sleeveless
* !post #8447845: [[cropped rash guard|cropped]]
* !post #4746757: worn with matching shorts

h4. See also

* [[swimsuit]]
* [[wetsuit]]
* [[Tag group:Attire]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Rash guard":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rash_guard]

title: wetsuit
body:
A protective [[bodysuit]] used in water activities such as [[surfing]] or [[scuba]] diving.

The main features that distinguish it from a [[unitard]] are an extended neck area or collar, multiple pieces with visible seams, or a sportier design.

Tag with [[male swimwear]] if used by a male character.

Not to be confused with a [[rash guard]].

To divert Sideroca from her self-destructive urge to train, [[Dobermann (arknights)|]] secretly convinced her to take care of the [[Doctor (arknights)|]]'s unfitness. She enthusiastically obliged and, to convince the Doctor to set foot in the gym, she quickly learnt how to cook to entice them with food in exchange of working out.

title: turing_love
body:
Song by [[Nayutalien]], with vocals by [[Nanawo Akari]] and featuring [[Sou (utaite)|]]. It was used as the ending theme to the animated adaptation of [[Rikei ga Koi ni Ochita no de Shoumeishitemita]].

The song features two official music videos: one "live action":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tBCuAatDPj4] with "Azukin Toki":[https://twitter.com/azukin_toki] and choreographer "Iriban-sensei":[https://twitter.com/panpaooo] dancing, and the other "with animated characters":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L-MVk5I6wjo] designed by [[Terada Tera]] (as with other Nayutailien / Nanawo Akari collaboriations). Those characters can be seen in post #4814546.

The latter video spun off a number of [[virtual Youtuber]], who all use the animated MV [[terada tera (style)|as inspiration]] for the cover videos.

There's also an "TV anime version song MV":https://youtube.com/watch?v=Y8FqZjq-Jb4 like all other anime EDs, but it's much less known and referenced.

title: utage_(arknights)
body:
[i]Utage, Guard Operator, is standing around on the front lines lazily.[/i]

A playable Guard Operator in [[Arknights]].

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Higashi[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]April 4[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Unknown[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]161 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]None[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

An ordinary student from Higashi. She came aboard Rhodes Island to treat her Oripathy, where applied to become an operator.

Cheerful and outgoing personality, she often hangs aroun other Higashi operators, such as [[Kirara (arknights)|]] and [[Akafuyu (arknights)|]]. She closely follows the market of the latest fashion trends and a lot of people come to her for advices on the topic. 

While her duties mostly consist of Logistics and HR, she has proven quite capable in combat where she exhibits a terrifying demeanor. She is able to completely mask her psychological state.

Her race and her [[katana]] are shrouded in mystery.

Her [[voice actor]]s are Yoshioka Mayu (Japanese), Xu Xu (Chinese), and Choi Ha-ri (Korean). Her art designer is [[kamameshi gougoumaru]].

h4. Skins

title: miguel_serverto
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. He appears in [[Gundam GQuuuuuux]] from 2025.

[b]Miguel Serverto[/b] is a [[Zeon]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] test pilot. [spoiler]A member of [[Gihren Zabi]]'s faction who successfuly poisoned to death two of his test pilot friends to delay research on the [[GFred]].[/spoiler] 

[spoiler]He is accidentally killed by [[nyaan_(gundam_gquuuuuux)|Nyaan]] (using the GFred's [[funnels_(gundam)|funnels]]) when he tries to shot her after she rejected his poisoned cake.[/spoiler]

title: jurick_(mobile_suit)
body:
A fictional manned giant combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared as a part of the [[Gundam MSV]]-R line.

[b]MSM-06 Jurick[/b]

An experimental gorilla-shaped amphibious [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]] from the Universal Century timeline. It combines characteristics (and weaponry) from both the [[Gogg]] and the [[Z'Gok]].

title: miyamoto_musashi_(fate)
body:
Saber-class servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. She's a genderswap of the famous samurai of the [[Miyamoto Musashi|same name]] who killed his first man in a duel at age 13,  founded the Niten Ichi-ryū (二天一流) style of swordsmanship and wrote The Book of Five Rings (五輪の書).

She has [[pink hair]] in a [[ponytail]] held by a fan-like [[hair ornament]], [[blue eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. Initially wears a [[blue kimono|blue]] [[sleeveless kimono]] with an [[obi]], black [[detached sleeves]], [[black thighhighs]], and [[sandals]]. Later her kimono becomes more elaborate, gaining a [[navel cutout]], a red cloth with a [[maple leaf print]], and more red details. The chest area is also revealed. Sometimes her sleeves are also [[wide sleeves|widened]]. She has maple [[earrings]] and [[dual wielding|wields two]] [[katana|katanas]] while keeping two more [[sheathed]] at her waist.

[b]Illustrator[/b]: [[Koyama Hirokazu]]
[b]Voice Actress[/b]: [[Sakura Ayane]]

title: nyaan_(gundam_gquuuuuux)
body:
Female character from [[Gundam GQuuuuuux]].
Voiced by [[Ishikawa Yui]].

[b]Nyaan[/b] is a young, tall and shy courier girl. [spoiler]It is revealed mid series that she is actually a powerful Newtype and former [[mobile_suit|MS]] pilot with skills superior to those of [[amate_yuzuriha|Machu]]. She is shown to form even a more powerful bond with the [[GQuuuuuux]] reaching Newtype levels as high -or even stronger- than those of [[Shuji Ito]].[/spoiler] 

[spoiler]After the disappearance of Ito and his [[Red Gundam]] in a mini-[[Zeknova]] event, Nyaan keeps [[conch_(gundam)|Conch]] as her pet and she is recruited by [[Zeon]], becoming a Newtype MS pilot for [[Kycilia Zabi]]'s faction, who gives her the [[GFred]].[/spoiler]

Her character design is similar to a younger [[Roux Louka]] from [[Gundam ZZ]].

title: omurice
body:
A Western-inspired Japanese dish that features [[rice]] cooked into an [[omelet]], forming a pouch, and usually topped with [[ketchup]]. The ketchup is often poured to spell out words (such as the intended eater's name).

Typically, the rice is "chicken rice" [[fried rice|fried]] in a pan with chicken and ketchup, but the ingredients can vary. Other variations include [i]omusoba[/i] substituting [[yakisoba]] for the rice and [i]omutako[/i] in Okinawa consisting of an omelet over taco rice.

Stories about the origin of omurice vary, but two such stories attribute its origin to Western-style restaurants. The first says it originated around the turn of the 20th century at Renga-tei in Ginza, Tokyo after the restaurant got the idea for it from chakin [[sushi]], which features sushi rice wrapped in a thin omelet. The second says it originated in 1925 at Hokkyokusei in Minami, Osaka when a cook decided to enliven a regular customer's order of an omelet with rice.

h4. Examples

* !post #6484430

h4. See also

title: voyager_(fate)
body:
[[Fate (series)|Fate series]] character. A Voyager-class Servant who appears in [[Fate/Requiem]] and [[Fate/Grand Order]].

He is a young boy with [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. In [[Fate/Requiem]], he is [[Utsumi Erice]]'s Voyager-class Servant, whose True Name is initially unknown. He is initially thought to be either Antoine de Saint-Euxpery or The Little Prince. His True Name is later revealed to be the space probe [i]Voyager[/i] that was launched in 1977, making him the youngest Heroic Spirit in the franchise.

He appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]] as a Foreigner-class Servant.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[NOCO (Adamas)|]]

title: honkai_impact_3rd
body:
Chinese mobile game developed by [[miHoYo]], part of the [[honkai_(series)|Honkai Universe]]. An alternate universe to [[Benghuai Xueyuan]], having many of the same characters but different stories. Also known as Honkai 3rd or Houkai 3.

[[Kiana Kaslana]] is the protagonist of the main story up until Part 2, where [[Female dreamseeker (honkai impact)|]] replace her.

The player is the protagonist of the secondary story known as Captain's Bizarre Adventure, being the [[Captain_(honkai_impact)|Captain]] of the heavy-class battleship Hyperion instead of [[Murata Himeko]] and traveling across many bubble worlds in the Sea of Quanta.

Since the two games are mostly unrelated, unless it's a collaboration, [b]do not[/b] tag [[Benghuai Xueyuan]] when uploading posts from official sites ("Twitter":[https://twitter.com/houkai3rd/],...), posts that have [b]崩坏3[/b]/[b]Honkai Impact 3[/b] logo or exclusive characters/battlesuits/outfits not from [[Benghuai Xueyuan]].

title: friday_(movie)
body:
[b]Friday[/b] is a 1995 Stoner comedy movie staring [[Ice Cube (rapper)|]], Chris Tucker and John Witherspoon. The movie follows Craig Jones(Ice Cube) a slacker who recently got fired on Friday while helping his friend Smokey(Tucker) get money he owns to a drug dealer before a deadline while dealing with the neighborhood bully Deebo. Other characters include Willie Jones(Witherspoon), Craig's father and an avid food lover who tries to help his son in his own eccentric way.

The movie was a hit and remembered for many quotable dialogues like "Daaaaaammmmm!" and "Bye Felisha". The movie would later received two sequels, [i]Next Friday[/i] in 2000 and [i]Friday After Next[/i] in 2002 with Ice Cube and Witherspoon reprising their roles except Tucker, who no longer does movies that promote drugs after becoming religious, with the role of Craig's friend in the sequels being played by Mike Epps as Craig's cousin, Daymond "Day-Day" Jones. A fourth film titled [i]This Friday[/i], is currently in the works with Ice Cube and Chris Tucker returning except John Witherspoon, who died in 2019.

title: war_fan
body:
A Japanese war fan is a fan designed for use in warfare. Several types of war fans were used by the samurai class of feudal Japan and each had a different look and purpose.

There are three kinds of war fan:

Gunsen (軍扇) were folding fans used by the average warriors to cool themselves off. They were made of wood, bronze, brass or a similar metal for the inner spokes, and often used thin iron or other metals for the outer spokes or cover, making them lightweight but strong. Warriors would hang their fans from a variety of places, most typically from the belt or the breastplate, though the latter often impeded the use of a sword or a bow. Example: post #2540638

[[Tessen]] (鉄扇) were folding fans with outer spokes made of heavy plates of iron which were designed to look like normal, harmless folding fans or solid clubs shaped to look like a closed fan. Samurai could take these to places where swords or other overt weapons were not allowed, and some swordsmanship schools included training in the use of the tessen as a weapon. The tessen was also used for fending off knives and darts, as a throwing weapon, and as an aid in swimming. Example: post #1904493

[[Gunbai]] (Gumbai), Gunpai (Gumpai) or dansen uchiwa (軍配) were large solid open fans that could be solid iron, metal with wooden core, or solid wood, which were carried by high-ranking officers. They were used to ward off arrows, as a sunshade, and to signal to troops. Also used by scoring referees in sumo wrestling matches. Example: post #1990137
